[Amit Varma]: Remember, that's Storytel with a single L, Storytel.com.

01:10:11.720 --> 01:10:15.600
[Amit Varma]: Welcome back to The Scene in The Unseen, I'm chatting with Manu Pillay about The Ivory

01:10:15.600 --> 01:10:19.800
[Amit Varma]: Throne, his book on Kerala, in particular, the house of Travancore.

01:10:19.800 --> 01:10:25.560
[Amit Varma]: And the book begins with a chapter on the most famous Verma of all time, Raja Ravi Verma,

01:10:25.560 --> 01:10:32.640
[Amit Varma]: which in many ways is a very apt sort of place to begin because his descendants basically

01:10:32.640 --> 01:10:34.640
[Amit Varma]: rule the rest of the book.

01:10:34.640 --> 01:10:43.480
[Amit Varma]: So tell me a bit about, you know, how Raja Ravi Verma coming up in the court of Ayilyam

01:10:43.480 --> 01:10:44.480
[Amit Varma]: Tirunel.

01:10:44.480 --> 01:10:45.480
[Guest]: Ayilyam Tirunel.

01:10:45.480 --> 01:10:51.360
[Amit Varma]: Ayilyam Tirunel and his wife Kalyani Pillay, who was one of those amachis who sort of a

01:10:51.360 --> 01:10:58.960
[Amit Varma]: very powerful consort to the king as such, but after his death, sort of fades away.

01:10:58.960 --> 01:11:03.320
[Amit Varma]: But an early patron of Raja Ravi Verma, who initially when he goes to the paint, I mean,

01:11:03.320 --> 01:11:09.040
[Amit Varma]: of course, because of his upbringing and everything, he is sort of taken in and patronized.

01:11:09.040 --> 01:11:12.320
[Amit Varma]: But people refuse to teach him painting, the established guys of the day.

01:11:12.320 --> 01:11:13.600
[Amit Varma]: And so what's happening there?

01:11:13.600 --> 01:11:18.000
[Guest]: So Ravi Verma belongs to a group of 10 odd families, which are called Koyildambirans.

01:11:18.000 --> 01:11:22.400
[Guest]: Koyildambirans are these ex-Rajas who immigrated from Malabar to Travancore.

01:11:22.400 --> 01:11:26.560
[Guest]: Most of them during the time Tipu Sultan invaded Malabar and they lost all their territories.

01:11:26.560 --> 01:11:29.520
[Guest]: So they accepted pensions afterwards from the British and they decided to just come

01:11:29.520 --> 01:11:30.520
[Guest]: and live in Travancore.

01:11:30.520 --> 01:11:34.440
[Guest]: Ravi Verma's family, however, was the oldest, which came in the 17th century.

01:11:34.440 --> 01:11:38.520
[Guest]: And they were famous for an entire, for like nearly a hundred years, all the kings of Travancore

01:11:38.520 --> 01:11:42.160
[Guest]: were fathered by men who were consorts to Travancore princesses.

01:11:42.160 --> 01:11:45.320
[Guest]: These consorts all, the male consorts all came from the Khilmanur family for a very

01:11:45.320 --> 01:11:46.320
[Guest]: long time.

01:11:46.320 --> 01:11:48.240
[Guest]: So Ravi Verma was born into this family.

01:11:48.240 --> 01:11:51.600
[Guest]: Now a lot of legend has sort of cloaked his story after he became famous.

01:11:51.600 --> 01:11:55.680
[Guest]: So there is a story, for example, that he was brought to court and he was rejected as

01:11:55.680 --> 01:11:58.000
[Guest]: a princess's husband because he was too dark.

01:11:58.000 --> 01:12:00.920
[Guest]: And how he said, oh, this was actually a wonderful thing because if he had been forced to marry

01:12:00.920 --> 01:12:04.640
[Guest]: a princess, he would never have been able to travel and discover his true calling.

01:12:04.640 --> 01:12:07.360
[Guest]: It's rubbish because by the time he came to the Travancore court, all the princesses were

01:12:07.360 --> 01:12:08.360
[Guest]: already married.

01:12:08.360 --> 01:12:11.080
[Guest]: So there was no question of marrying a royal princess.

01:12:11.080 --> 01:12:15.920
[Guest]: It's one of those later stories, masala that people add to the stories of famous men.

01:12:15.920 --> 01:12:20.960
[Guest]: Even the story that, you know, he was some sort of self-taught genius in an artless universe

01:12:20.960 --> 01:12:24.520
[Guest]: and he had to sort of struggle against the odds is exaggerated in some ways because there

01:12:24.520 --> 01:12:26.080
[Guest]: was a lot of art in Travancore.

01:12:26.080 --> 01:12:27.960
[Guest]: He was exposed to a lot of things.

01:12:27.960 --> 01:12:31.280
[Guest]: For a long time, there was a painter called Ramaswamy Naidu, there was before him a man

01:12:31.280 --> 01:12:32.280
[Guest]: called Alagiri Naidu.

01:12:32.280 --> 01:12:36.240
[Guest]: These people were men of talent who, you know, far surpassed him for a very long period.

01:12:36.240 --> 01:12:40.080
[Guest]: But he did something very unusual, which is that Ravi Verma never got satisfied with court

01:12:40.080 --> 01:12:42.280
[Guest]: settings and the patronage of one court.

01:12:42.280 --> 01:12:47.120
[Guest]: He was there for 18 years, 1862 till the death of this king called Ayalayam Tirunel in 1880.

01:12:47.120 --> 01:12:51.320
[Guest]: The successor king did not like Ravi Verma, so Ravi Verma had no option but to leave.

01:12:51.320 --> 01:12:52.320
[Guest]: Then he does something.

01:12:52.320 --> 01:12:53.560
[Guest]: He takes advantage of the railways.

01:12:53.560 --> 01:12:55.480
[Guest]: He takes advantage of patronage.

01:12:55.480 --> 01:12:57.280
[Guest]: He's getting, you know, people are moving around.

01:12:57.280 --> 01:13:00.480
[Guest]: In India, it's finally possible to move around with great ease.

01:13:00.480 --> 01:13:04.040
[Guest]: So former Diwan of Travancore from a chief minister called Madhav Rao is now Diwan in

01:13:04.040 --> 01:13:05.040
[Guest]: Baroda.

01:13:05.040 --> 01:13:08.000
[Guest]: He uses that to bounce and get a painting commission in Baroda.

01:13:08.000 --> 01:13:09.360
[Guest]: Then he gets another one in Mysore.

01:13:09.360 --> 01:13:13.420
[Guest]: That's how Ravi Verma becomes this pan-Indian figure and leaves the Travancore setting.

01:13:13.420 --> 01:13:17.000
[Guest]: If he had stayed content as a Darbar artist, he would never have become famous.

01:13:17.000 --> 01:13:18.320
[Guest]: It was not purely talent.

01:13:18.320 --> 01:13:20.720
[Guest]: Perhaps there were more talented men than him in the Darbar.

01:13:20.720 --> 01:13:22.480
[Guest]: He's the one who made an opportunity out of it.

01:13:22.480 --> 01:13:26.200
[Guest]: He saw an opportunity, recognized it for what it was and worked like a professional.

01:13:26.200 --> 01:13:29.760
[Guest]: He diligently stuck to deadlines as far as he could.

01:13:29.760 --> 01:13:32.000
[Guest]: He delivered on promises he made.

01:13:32.000 --> 01:13:36.280
[Guest]: He traveled, hustled, you know, even when he became famous, he once went to get a commission

01:13:36.280 --> 01:13:37.760
[Guest]: from the Nizam of Hyderabad.

01:13:37.760 --> 01:13:39.320
[Guest]: He was by then a very famous artist.

01:13:39.320 --> 01:13:42.640
[Guest]: So Nizam made him wait for two hours and then finally just brushed him away.

01:13:42.640 --> 01:13:47.280
[Guest]: But Ravi Verma's willingness to hustle is really something because, you know, that professional

01:13:47.280 --> 01:13:49.440
[Guest]: ethic is not something that was linked to his background.

01:13:49.440 --> 01:13:51.040
[Guest]: He came from a feudal background.

01:13:51.040 --> 01:13:53.800
[Guest]: He had no reason to live a professional life like this.

01:13:53.800 --> 01:13:58.000
[Guest]: What is interesting with the Travancore royal family and him though is that how his quest

01:13:58.000 --> 01:14:02.240
[Guest]: to sort of build a career causes a lot of animosity in his personal life.

01:14:02.240 --> 01:14:07.120
[Guest]: Now Ravi Verma's wife is the grandmother of the future Maharanis of Travancore, Setu Lakshmi

01:14:07.120 --> 01:14:12.160
[Guest]: and Setu Parvati guy and there her marriage with Ravi Verma is extremely turbulent.

01:14:12.160 --> 01:14:14.280
[Guest]: This woman to begin with is from an aristocratic family.

01:14:14.280 --> 01:14:17.000
[Guest]: She does not understand why her husband needs a profession.

01:14:17.000 --> 01:14:20.480
[Guest]: More scandalizingly, she doesn't know why on earth he wants to be a painter of all things

01:14:20.480 --> 01:14:22.520
[Guest]: because painters were seen as artisans.

01:14:22.520 --> 01:14:26.280
[Guest]: They were not seen as artists, you know, signing your name is an innovation and that he really

01:14:26.280 --> 01:14:29.920
[Guest]: begins in Travancore and brings a certain respect to it, partly also because of his

01:14:29.920 --> 01:14:30.920
[Amit Varma]: class.

01:14:30.920 --> 01:14:36.480
[Amit Varma]: And the combination of using the lithograph to spread his work and, you know, signing

01:14:36.480 --> 01:14:41.880
[Guest]: his name just, you know, as a branding exercise, you know, unprecedented.

01:14:41.880 --> 01:14:44.040
[Guest]: But he also uses his class and caste connections.

01:14:44.040 --> 01:14:47.480
[Guest]: The thing is, Ravi Verma, because he belongs to these families, it supplies husbands to

01:14:47.480 --> 01:14:48.480
[Guest]: royalty.

01:14:48.480 --> 01:14:50.760
[Guest]: He is essentially in many ways an aristocrat.

01:14:50.760 --> 01:14:52.600
[Guest]: He's part of the cream of society.

01:14:52.600 --> 01:14:55.000
[Guest]: So wherever he goes, he's not treated as an artisan.

01:14:55.000 --> 01:14:56.720
[Guest]: He's treated as a gentleman artist.

01:14:56.720 --> 01:15:00.320
[Guest]: And that's a very new sort of concept for an Indian painter in the late 19th century.

01:15:00.320 --> 01:15:02.200
[Guest]: Now, the thing is, the wife doesn't like this.

01:15:02.200 --> 01:15:04.400
[Guest]: It also means a lot of separation from her.

01:15:04.400 --> 01:15:07.640
[Guest]: There's a charming story, but not charming, really, but a very telling story about how

01:15:07.640 --> 01:15:10.000
[Guest]: he once has disappeared for a long time.

01:15:10.000 --> 01:15:11.880
[Guest]: Then he finally comes back to his wife's place.

01:15:11.880 --> 01:15:15.800
[Guest]: And as usual, as a matrilineal husband, he has to go to his wife's place to meet her.

01:15:15.800 --> 01:15:19.240
[Guest]: And she's gone for a bath or something, or she's gone to the temple or something.

01:15:19.240 --> 01:15:22.000
[Guest]: And he's got this wonderful Italian chandelier to hang up there.

01:15:22.000 --> 01:15:24.800
[Guest]: He tells all the servants to go ahead and put this up before she comes back from the

01:15:24.800 --> 01:15:25.800
[Guest]: temple visit.

01:15:25.800 --> 01:15:27.720
[Guest]: So it's a surprise for her.

01:15:27.720 --> 01:15:31.560
[Guest]: The lady comes back, she takes one look at this well lit, beautiful, expensive chandelier

01:15:31.560 --> 01:15:35.240
[Guest]: he's got from some god knows which Maharaja or the other, commands her servants to pull

01:15:35.240 --> 01:15:37.000
[Guest]: it down and throws it out of the window.

01:15:37.000 --> 01:15:38.800
[Guest]: And she smashes it because she doesn't care.

01:15:38.800 --> 01:15:40.520
[Guest]: She's like, you know, you've not been here for two years.

01:15:40.520 --> 01:15:44.040
[Guest]: I don't know, you can just waltz in with a chandelier and think that the present is going

01:15:44.040 --> 01:15:45.040
[Guest]: to sort this out.

01:15:45.040 --> 01:15:46.040
[Guest]: It's not.

01:15:46.040 --> 01:15:49.520
[Guest]: She also, there's a record from her nephew talking about how she got addicted to alcohol.

01:15:49.520 --> 01:15:52.720
[Guest]: Now, her sisters were already by that time, Maharanis of Travancore.

01:15:52.720 --> 01:15:54.680
[Guest]: So she's essentially in their shadow on the one hand.

01:15:54.680 --> 01:15:56.800
[Guest]: She's also got a husband who neglects her.

01:15:56.800 --> 01:15:59.480
[Guest]: And you know, she's therefore seemed to have a very difficult life.

01:15:59.480 --> 01:16:03.520
[Guest]: And she dies a very untimely death in her mid thirties, you know, she dies a very young

01:16:03.520 --> 01:16:04.520
[Guest]: woman.

01:16:04.520 --> 01:16:07.240
[Guest]: Now, Ravi Verma has three daughters and two sons.

01:16:07.240 --> 01:16:08.920
[Guest]: One daughter really doesn't come into the picture.

01:16:08.920 --> 01:16:12.160
[Guest]: The oldest son becomes a drunkard, disappears in 1912.

01:16:12.160 --> 01:16:13.160
[Guest]: Nobody knows what happened to him.

01:16:13.160 --> 01:16:16.360
[Guest]: There's a story that he disappeared into Goa and he married a Konkani Christian and there

01:16:16.360 --> 01:16:19.760
[Guest]: are Christian descendants of Ravi Verma in Goa, but nobody's really heard of them after

01:16:19.760 --> 01:16:20.760
[Guest]: that.

01:16:20.760 --> 01:16:23.200
[Guest]: The second son goes to the JJ School of Art, learns art, etc.

01:16:23.200 --> 01:16:25.500
[Guest]: But has only a fraction of his father's talent.

01:16:25.500 --> 01:16:27.000
[Guest]: He doesn't become a famous name.

01:16:27.000 --> 01:16:30.880
[Guest]: And he never manages to leave the Travancore Darbar in Kerala and get stuck in that court

01:16:30.880 --> 01:16:31.880
[Guest]: environment.

01:16:31.880 --> 01:16:32.880
[Guest]: So he's not famous.

01:16:32.880 --> 01:16:35.640
[Guest]: Of the two daughters, this is where the politics comes.

01:16:35.640 --> 01:16:39.640
[Guest]: Now, Manjalis have the word Soundarya Panakam for it, beauty wars, you know, small little

01:16:39.640 --> 01:16:41.680
[Guest]: petty disputes in the family.

01:16:41.680 --> 01:16:45.000
[Guest]: The older daughter is not only good looking, she's extremely imperious.

01:16:45.000 --> 01:16:49.040
[Guest]: And the mother's untimely death means that she becomes the de facto head of the family.

01:16:49.040 --> 01:16:50.320
[Guest]: The father's anyway traveling, etc.

01:16:50.320 --> 01:16:54.200
[Guest]: So this eldest girl steps up and becomes the main force in the family.

01:16:54.200 --> 01:16:57.720
[Guest]: That she's beautiful and imperious further adds to her personality.

01:16:57.720 --> 01:17:01.440
[Guest]: The second daughter is not only not beautiful, she's got a squint, she's dark skinned and

01:17:01.440 --> 01:17:06.080
[Guest]: she's therefore seen as the not pretty sister in the family.

01:17:06.080 --> 01:17:07.080
[Guest]: The youngest one's also good looking.

01:17:07.080 --> 01:17:11.360
[Guest]: So the middle sister's got this inferiority complex, you know, of sorts that she's not

01:17:11.360 --> 01:17:14.740
[Guest]: not only she's not the main person in the family, her sister's the head of the family.

01:17:14.740 --> 01:17:16.520
[Guest]: She's not even good looking.

01:17:16.520 --> 01:17:20.680
[Guest]: Now it is these two sisters, their daughters, who get adopted into the Travancore royal

01:17:20.680 --> 01:17:25.240
[Guest]: family because the Travancore family has kings and princes, but it's run out of females.

01:17:25.240 --> 01:17:26.840
[Guest]: Whenever that happens, they adopt girls.

01:17:26.840 --> 01:17:29.880
[Guest]: In North Indian families, they adopt boys from various families.

01:17:29.880 --> 01:17:31.400
[Guest]: But in this case, they adopt girl children.

01:17:31.400 --> 01:17:34.120
[Amit Varma]: So if they don't have daughters, they'll adopt girls.

01:17:34.120 --> 01:17:38.880
[Amit Varma]: And the backstory to this is that earlier the two people, the two girls they adopted

01:17:38.880 --> 01:17:43.000
[Amit Varma]: were the sisters of Bhagirathi, who was Raja Ravi Varma's wife.

01:17:43.000 --> 01:17:48.080
[Amit Varma]: And therefore, they have an interest, especially the older one of them, who is Lakshmibai and

01:17:48.080 --> 01:17:51.920
[Amit Varma]: earlier Lakshmibai, not the heroine of our story.

01:17:51.920 --> 01:17:59.040
[Amit Varma]: And she has an interest in getting her nieces, so to say, adopted into the grand nieces,

01:17:59.040 --> 01:18:00.040
[Guest]: her grandchildren.

01:18:00.040 --> 01:18:05.040
[Guest]: Basically, there were three sisters in the Mavelikara aristocratic family of royal descent

01:18:05.040 --> 01:18:06.040
[Guest]: from North Kerala.

01:18:06.040 --> 01:18:08.920
[Guest]: Two were adopted in the mid 19th century into the Travancore family.

01:18:08.920 --> 01:18:11.280
[Guest]: The one who was not adopted is Ravi Varma's wife.

01:18:11.280 --> 01:18:14.640
[Guest]: Now a few two generations pass, one of these queens has no children.

01:18:14.640 --> 01:18:17.360
[Guest]: The other queen has only sons, no surviving daughters.

01:18:17.360 --> 01:18:20.680
[Guest]: So the adoption is proof pointless because you've produced boys and boys will rule, but

01:18:20.680 --> 01:18:22.480
[Guest]: boys will not take the family forward.

01:18:22.480 --> 01:18:23.880
[Guest]: So you need to adopt girls again.

01:18:23.880 --> 01:18:25.000
[Guest]: So who do they turn to?

01:18:25.000 --> 01:18:27.760
[Guest]: The grandchildren of their third sister, who wasn't adopted.

01:18:27.760 --> 01:18:30.400
[Guest]: Those grandchildren are then brought into the family.

01:18:30.400 --> 01:18:35.040
[Guest]: But now the funny thing is this adoption is fraught with complications because in the

01:18:35.040 --> 01:18:38.760
[Guest]: Travancore royal family itself, the heir apparent, who then dies very soon after, some say he

01:18:38.760 --> 01:18:41.640
[Guest]: was poisoned to death, but there's no proof.

01:18:41.640 --> 01:18:44.680
[Guest]: He basically objects to these girls being adopted for several reasons.

01:18:44.680 --> 01:18:47.760
[Guest]: He says their grandmother, that is Ravi Varma's wife, was addicted to alcohol.

01:18:47.760 --> 01:18:48.760
[Amit Varma]: So this is not a good family.

01:18:48.760 --> 01:18:49.760
[Amit Varma]: And her brother, in fact.

01:18:49.760 --> 01:18:50.760
[Amit Varma]: And her brother.

01:18:50.760 --> 01:18:51.760
[Guest]: There's cancer in the family.

01:18:51.760 --> 01:18:53.680
[Guest]: That's why, you know, that's also not a good thing.

01:18:53.680 --> 01:18:56.440
[Guest]: He thinks these girls are not suitable to be adopted.

01:18:56.440 --> 01:18:59.260
[Guest]: Some say Ravi Varma used his influence on Lord Curzon, the Viceroy.

01:18:59.260 --> 01:19:02.880
[Guest]: But the fact is that then Maharaja was keen on these girls, so they get it done.

01:19:02.880 --> 01:19:06.840
[Guest]: One interesting thing, which I discovered after I wrote the book, and which really took

01:19:06.840 --> 01:19:11.640
[Guest]: me aback, and it's funny how not a single biographer, even the most authoritative biography

01:19:11.640 --> 01:19:15.040
[Guest]: of Ravi Varma by Rupika Chawla does not have this story, and it's not made it to my book

01:19:15.040 --> 01:19:19.120
[Guest]: because I found it afterwards, is that there's one more scandal in Ravi Varma's family, which

01:19:19.120 --> 01:19:21.800
[Guest]: was that his father-in-law was a murderer.

01:19:21.800 --> 01:19:26.200
[Guest]: So Ravi Varma's mother-in-law, there's this magnificent painting he's done of this lady.

01:19:26.200 --> 01:19:30.340
[Guest]: You know, he's, this lady is, you know, he's famous for painting all these fair-skinned

01:19:30.340 --> 01:19:32.580
[Guest]: Indian classical beauties, as it were.

01:19:32.580 --> 01:19:34.680
[Guest]: This lady is not only fair-skinned, she's dark-skinned.

01:19:34.680 --> 01:19:40.200
[Guest]: She has bloodshot eyes, a mane of really like white silver hair, glaring out of the painting.

01:19:40.200 --> 01:19:43.880
[Guest]: He's got a bulbous nose, not a classical Ravi Varma beauty you'd expect.

01:19:43.880 --> 01:19:47.280
[Guest]: But he's, this one painting, I think, is the most striking portrait he's done because he's

01:19:47.280 --> 01:19:49.760
[Guest]: depicted his mother-in-law exactly as she was.

01:19:49.760 --> 01:19:53.200
[Guest]: Some say he's actually softened her appearance because she's a ferocious looking woman in

01:19:53.200 --> 01:19:54.200
[Guest]: this painting.

01:19:54.200 --> 01:19:59.320
[Guest]: It was in the Travancore royal family, now I think in a private collection in Bangalore.

01:19:59.320 --> 01:20:04.680
[Guest]: And this lady apparently was having, there's a story that she had a servant called Madhavan,

01:20:04.680 --> 01:20:06.440
[Guest]: and one day Madhavan was found killed.

01:20:06.440 --> 01:20:10.240
[Guest]: The official story was he'd stolen 12 pieces of jewelry, so her husband caught him and

01:20:10.240 --> 01:20:11.800
[Guest]: beat him up and murdered him.

01:20:11.800 --> 01:20:16.440
[Guest]: Now the official who actually investigated it found that the murder was highly sadistic.

01:20:16.440 --> 01:20:19.640
[Guest]: Someone had tried to gouge out his eyes, a massive jackfruit had been like used to beat

01:20:19.640 --> 01:20:23.760
[Guest]: him up and this, and then they tried to hang up the body or put it in a, in a, in a pond.

01:20:23.760 --> 01:20:27.240
[Guest]: It's not clear what exactly happened, but they tried to make it look like suicide.

01:20:27.240 --> 01:20:30.040
[Guest]: And this particular official said the police is not doing a good job of the investigation.

01:20:30.040 --> 01:20:32.120
[Guest]: They're trying to cover this up as a suicide.

01:20:32.120 --> 01:20:33.120
[Guest]: Why are they doing this?

01:20:33.120 --> 01:20:34.120
[Guest]: This is all in 1862.

01:20:34.120 --> 01:20:36.520
[Guest]: This is a covered up suicide in Mavelikara.

01:20:36.520 --> 01:20:40.280
[Guest]: And the senior official says, no, this has to be investigated properly.

01:20:40.280 --> 01:20:44.520
[Guest]: And they discover in the Cochin Courier, there's a newspaper that says that Ravi Arma's father-in-law

01:20:44.520 --> 01:20:48.400
[Guest]: suspected this lady, this ferocious lady in the painting, of having an affair with this

01:20:48.400 --> 01:20:49.400
[Guest]: servant called Madhavan.

01:20:49.400 --> 01:20:52.560
[Guest]: And that is why he killed him in this sadistic fashion.

01:20:52.560 --> 01:20:53.560
[Guest]: And the man was tried.

01:20:53.560 --> 01:20:56.600
[Guest]: He was taken to court and he was sentenced to life imprisonment.

01:20:56.600 --> 01:21:00.440
[Guest]: And this is not mentioned in any of Ravi Arma's biographies that his father-in-law was essentially

01:21:00.440 --> 01:21:04.200
[Guest]: stuck in jail and that his mother-in-law was part of one of the big sex scandals of the

01:21:04.200 --> 01:21:06.680
[Guest]: of the 1860s as it were.

01:21:06.680 --> 01:21:10.880
[Guest]: So anyway, so there's all sorts of chaos and problems in Ravi Arma's family.

01:21:10.880 --> 01:21:13.880
[Guest]: Yet in 1900, these two girls are adopted.

01:21:13.880 --> 01:21:17.800
[Amit Varma]: Which are basically the elder daughter of Ravi Arma, you mentioned is Maha Prabha and

01:21:17.800 --> 01:21:19.240
[Amit Varma]: she's a fair and beautiful one.

01:21:19.240 --> 01:21:21.560
[Amit Varma]: And her daughter is Setu Lakshmibai.

01:21:21.560 --> 01:21:25.960
[Amit Varma]: And the other one, yeah, and the middle daughter, I can't pronounce her name, Kuchukuni.

01:21:25.960 --> 01:21:30.600
[Guest]: So her daughter is Setu Parvati Bai, who were adopted as senior and junior Rani of Travel

01:21:30.600 --> 01:21:31.600
[Guest]: Corps.

01:21:31.600 --> 01:21:32.600
[Guest]: Senior and junior Rani.

01:21:32.600 --> 01:21:36.720
[Guest]: Now, this brings in, now, there was already politics between the sisters, you know, their

01:21:36.720 --> 01:21:37.720
[Guest]: mothers did not get along.

01:21:37.720 --> 01:21:39.520
[Guest]: Their mothers were, had their own issues.

01:21:39.520 --> 01:21:41.520
[Guest]: Now, this translates to the children as well.

01:21:41.520 --> 01:21:45.640
[Guest]: Because what happens is Setu Lakshmibai, the older one is the fair-skinned, perfect child.

01:21:45.640 --> 01:21:46.920
[Guest]: She's very good at her exam.

01:21:46.920 --> 01:21:49.360
[Guest]: She's very diligent, very obedient.

01:21:49.360 --> 01:21:50.360
[Guest]: Teachers all love her.

01:21:50.360 --> 01:21:52.120
[Guest]: And as senior Rani, she's very proper.

01:21:52.120 --> 01:21:55.280
[Guest]: She's just like perfect senior Rani, does everything perfectly.

01:21:55.280 --> 01:21:56.680
[Guest]: But she doesn't enjoy the limelight.

01:21:56.680 --> 01:21:58.160
[Guest]: So she's a very shy woman.

01:21:58.160 --> 01:21:59.160
[Guest]: So people find it sweet.

01:21:59.160 --> 01:22:01.400
[Guest]: You know, she's in a position of influence, but she's also shy.

01:22:01.400 --> 01:22:05.360
[Guest]: So like this, this evolving idea of ideal of Indian womanhood, which is that women should

01:22:05.360 --> 01:22:06.360
[Guest]: be a certain way.

01:22:06.360 --> 01:22:09.360
[Guest]: She seems to fit all these new notions of what a girl should be.

01:22:09.360 --> 01:22:13.880
[Amit Varma]: And what you also, you know, describe in your book is how shortly after these two are adapted,

01:22:13.880 --> 01:22:17.280
[Amit Varma]: there are three deaths in the family, which is both the sons die.

01:22:17.280 --> 01:22:20.080
[Amit Varma]: And then the senior Lakshmibai dies as well.

01:22:20.080 --> 01:22:26.280
[Amit Varma]: And therefore, Setu Lakshmibai at the age of 10, at the age of 5, is a de facto queen

01:22:26.280 --> 01:22:27.280
[Guest]: of Trivandrum.

01:22:27.280 --> 01:22:30.920
[Guest]: So now this causes issues for her cousin, because her cousin is the junior Rani.

01:22:30.920 --> 01:22:36.920
[Guest]: Now implicit in that title itself is junior, your junior, she's just a year younger.

01:22:36.920 --> 01:22:40.080
[Guest]: And frankly, she has more of a personality to be queen.

01:22:40.080 --> 01:22:43.840
[Guest]: She's rebellious, unorthodox, you know, she's the first person in the Trivandrum royal family

01:22:43.840 --> 01:22:47.840
[Guest]: to take her daughter and go abroad for the first time, cross the Kala Pani on her own.

01:22:47.840 --> 01:22:51.200
[Guest]: She goes to meet the Pope and the Pope's secretary says, oh, you know, with the Pope, you can't

01:22:51.200 --> 01:22:52.200
[Guest]: really wear makeup, etc.

01:22:52.200 --> 01:22:53.880
[Guest]: You have to be dressed a certain way.

01:22:53.880 --> 01:22:57.280
[Guest]: And she tells him to essentially buzz off and say that she'll dress exactly as she wants

01:22:57.280 --> 01:22:58.280
[Guest]: in front of the Pope.

01:22:58.280 --> 01:23:01.840
[Guest]: In the 1930s, Trivandrum is an orthodox temple town.

01:23:01.840 --> 01:23:06.640
[Guest]: And this lady has the gall really to bring Margaret Sanger, the great birth control activist

01:23:06.640 --> 01:23:10.320
[Guest]: who even cheesed off Gandhiji, to come to this temple town and address a gathering full

01:23:10.320 --> 01:23:13.000
[Guest]: of men and about the advantages of birth control.

01:23:13.000 --> 01:23:17.280
[Guest]: She's a very spunky, interesting lady, her politics is extremely complicated, but as

01:23:17.280 --> 01:23:19.680
[Guest]: a person, remarkable figure.

01:23:19.680 --> 01:23:24.080
[Guest]: So you have a senior Rani who officially holds the limelight, who's very shy and retiring

01:23:24.080 --> 01:23:28.120
[Guest]: and is very sweet, but does not have, you know, this kind of rebellious personality.

01:23:28.120 --> 01:23:33.200
[Guest]: You have the junior who hates being in the shadow, who hates being not in the limelight,

01:23:33.200 --> 01:23:37.760
[Guest]: who wants the limelight and who has the personality for it, but she's stuck in a junior position.

01:23:37.760 --> 01:23:42.320
[Guest]: And although they're only five years old at the time, six and just about five, one year's

01:23:42.320 --> 01:23:44.200
[Guest]: age difference.

01:23:44.200 --> 01:23:47.320
[Guest]: Although they're children, they're seen by the people as institutions.

01:23:47.320 --> 01:23:50.160
[Guest]: They're not little girls, they're senior Rani and junior Rani.

01:23:50.160 --> 01:23:52.360
[Guest]: So from the beginning, there is protocol around them.

01:23:52.360 --> 01:23:56.760
[Guest]: From the beginning, you know, they have to visit and meet state visitors and governors

01:23:56.760 --> 01:23:57.760
[Amit Varma]: and viceroys and people.

01:23:57.760 --> 01:23:58.760
[Amit Varma]: And childhood is gone.

01:23:58.760 --> 01:23:59.760
[Amit Varma]: They can't stay with friends.

01:23:59.760 --> 01:24:00.760
[Guest]: There is no, they have no friends.

01:24:00.760 --> 01:24:01.760
[Guest]: There is no notion of childhood.

01:24:01.760 --> 01:24:05.320
[Guest]: They're not even allowed to see their families except, you know, every six months their families

01:24:05.320 --> 01:24:06.480
[Guest]: can come and stay.

01:24:06.480 --> 01:24:08.320
[Guest]: But otherwise, they can't really have any access.

01:24:08.320 --> 01:24:11.000
[Amit Varma]: Even their fathers have to, you know, their fathers have to bow to them.

01:24:11.000 --> 01:24:16.520
[Guest]: You know, they can't, you know, you can't call your daughter by name.

01:24:16.520 --> 01:24:17.920
[Guest]: She is now her highness to you.

01:24:17.920 --> 01:24:20.120
[Guest]: You can't really touch her head and pretend she's your daughter.

01:24:20.120 --> 01:24:25.200
[Guest]: I mean, private, perhaps you can, but basically a lot of protocol comes into their life.

01:24:25.200 --> 01:24:29.520
[Guest]: Now they grew up, they get their tutors and governesses, and they're raised in a certain

01:24:29.520 --> 01:24:30.520
[Guest]: way.

01:24:30.520 --> 01:24:31.520
[Guest]: Now marriage comes into this.

01:24:31.520 --> 01:24:34.000
[Guest]: Now, already one is evolving into this good looking pretty one.

01:24:34.000 --> 01:24:36.140
[Guest]: The other one is not, you know, like her mother.

01:24:36.140 --> 01:24:37.140
[Guest]: She's darker.

01:24:37.140 --> 01:24:38.140
[Guest]: In fact, she's dark.

01:24:38.140 --> 01:24:41.120
[Guest]: During the adoption, a senior courtier even said she's too black to be a princess.

01:24:41.120 --> 01:24:44.480
[Guest]: There's an actual record of this, that this girl should not be adopted because she's too

01:24:44.480 --> 01:24:46.320
[Guest]: dark and she doesn't look royal enough.

01:24:46.320 --> 01:24:49.880
[Guest]: So you can imagine she's obviously affected by this constant comparison with her seemingly

01:24:49.880 --> 01:24:51.760
[Guest]: perfect older sister.

01:24:51.760 --> 01:24:52.760
[Guest]: Now marriage happens.

01:24:52.760 --> 01:24:53.760
[Guest]: How does marriage happen?

01:24:53.760 --> 01:24:55.640
[Guest]: Boys are presented to these girls.

01:24:55.640 --> 01:24:58.960
[Guest]: So the senior Rani is presented two brothers and she's made to look from a balcony and

01:24:58.960 --> 01:25:01.200
[Guest]: choose whichever one she likes of the two brothers.

01:25:01.200 --> 01:25:03.520
[Guest]: One would think that in courts, horoscopes, etc. matter.

01:25:03.520 --> 01:25:04.520
[Guest]: No.

01:25:04.520 --> 01:25:05.520
[Guest]: The Rani chooses who she wants.

01:25:05.520 --> 01:25:07.440
[Guest]: It's the job of the astrologer to make the horoscope match.

01:25:07.440 --> 01:25:08.440
[Guest]: Otherwise he loses his job.

01:25:08.440 --> 01:25:09.440
[Guest]: That's how it works.

01:25:09.440 --> 01:25:10.760
[Guest]: So she looks at these two boys.

01:25:10.760 --> 01:25:13.440
[Guest]: The older one is this 20 year old, very handsome man.

01:25:13.440 --> 01:25:14.440
[Guest]: She says she's a 10 year old girl.

01:25:14.440 --> 01:25:15.440
[Guest]: She's like, no, no, no.

01:25:15.440 --> 01:25:16.440
[Guest]: This one is too much for me.

01:25:16.440 --> 01:25:20.360
[Guest]: She chooses this diminutive looking 16 year old, you know, slightly salki looking, less

01:25:20.360 --> 01:25:21.360
[Guest]: handsome brother.

01:25:21.360 --> 01:25:24.880
[Amit Varma]: Which surprises everyone because basically the older boy, as you describe him, and he's

01:25:24.880 --> 01:25:29.320
[Amit Varma]: even depicted in a Raja Ravi Verma painting, which I then googled to see what it's like,

01:25:29.320 --> 01:25:31.360
[Amit Varma]: is basically a bare chested Virat Kohli.

01:25:31.360 --> 01:25:32.360
[Guest]: He is.

01:25:32.360 --> 01:25:35.660
[Guest]: In fact, there's one painting that's not in the book of him.

01:25:35.660 --> 01:25:39.800
[Guest]: He's sort of, you know, he held his hands like this, he's folded against his chest.

01:25:39.800 --> 01:25:43.320
[Guest]: And he's again shirtless and he's got his hair let loose a little bit.

01:25:43.320 --> 01:25:47.400
[Guest]: And he's wearing a typical sort of munda around his waist and he's shirtless and he's looking

01:25:47.400 --> 01:25:51.280
[Guest]: out like that at the viewer of the painting and it's painted by Ravi Verma and he's strikingly

01:25:51.280 --> 01:25:52.280
[Guest]: good.

01:25:52.280 --> 01:25:53.280
[Guest]: I mean, that's a wonderful painting.

01:25:53.280 --> 01:25:57.160
[Guest]: Like he's, it's odd that in the early 20th century, this man clearly worked out a lot

01:25:57.160 --> 01:25:59.000
[Guest]: because he's got the muscles and all of that.

01:25:59.000 --> 01:26:02.840
[Guest]: Yeah, because this is a time when you know, status was in the size of your potbelly.

01:26:02.840 --> 01:26:07.520
[Amit Varma]: I'm like, this is your local Bollywood wannabe in the Lokhandwala gym.

01:26:07.520 --> 01:26:12.320
[Guest]: So there's the painting you refer to is the Ravi Verma painting called Shri Rama vanquishes

01:26:12.320 --> 01:26:15.680
[Unknown]: the sea in which this one models as Rama for Ravi Verma.

01:26:15.680 --> 01:26:17.800
[Guest]: So he is not chosen, his brother is chosen.

01:26:17.800 --> 01:26:21.840
[Guest]: His brother later gets smallpox and his face is completely left with pockmarks and he's

01:26:21.840 --> 01:26:23.960
[Guest]: not a very handsome man, but he's a very shrewd man.

01:26:23.960 --> 01:26:25.720
[Guest]: And the brother's name is Rama Verma.

01:26:25.720 --> 01:26:28.680
[Guest]: He's called the Valya Koil Tambaram, the senior consort, because he's married to the senior

01:26:28.680 --> 01:26:29.680
[Guest]: Rani.

01:26:29.680 --> 01:26:32.720
[Guest]: Now junior Rani the next year has offered husband choices for herself.

01:26:32.720 --> 01:26:34.160
[Guest]: She's offered five men.

01:26:34.160 --> 01:26:38.000
[Guest]: She decides to go and marry a good looking man who's also unfortunately the oldest, he's

01:26:38.000 --> 01:26:39.720
[Guest]: about 11 years older than her.

01:26:39.720 --> 01:26:42.760
[Guest]: But she says, look, he's already got a BA degree, he's a graduate from a university

01:26:42.760 --> 01:26:43.760
[Guest]: and all that.

01:26:43.760 --> 01:26:44.760
[Guest]: So he must be a good pick.

01:26:44.760 --> 01:26:48.560
[Guest]: And she marries him, which is a chap called Ravi Verma, which is also called Ravi Verma.

01:26:48.560 --> 01:26:51.040
[Guest]: He's the Kochi Koil Tambaram, the junior consort.

01:26:51.040 --> 01:26:54.320
[Guest]: Now the thing is, the marriages turn out very interestingly for both women.

01:26:54.320 --> 01:26:57.520
[Guest]: The senior Rani is married to this man and she is devoted to her husband.

01:26:57.520 --> 01:27:01.600
[Guest]: He has the personality to go out, he picks up now that he's picked up from a rural part

01:27:01.600 --> 01:27:05.840
[Guest]: of Kerala and planted in the palace, he starts learning English and he starts reading a lot.

01:27:05.840 --> 01:27:09.480
[Guest]: He starts riding, he acquires skills at shooting and sports and things like that.

01:27:09.480 --> 01:27:11.480
[Guest]: He enjoys this royal life.

01:27:11.480 --> 01:27:12.760
[Guest]: And she's devoted to him.

01:27:12.760 --> 01:27:15.480
[Guest]: And she finds that he's really good at the limelight and all of that.

01:27:15.480 --> 01:27:18.240
[Guest]: So she starts increasingly supporting her husband.

01:27:18.240 --> 01:27:22.680
[Guest]: Junior Rani's husband, although they get married at 10, the marriage is only consummated at

01:27:22.680 --> 01:27:23.680
[Guest]: 14.

01:27:23.680 --> 01:27:24.680
[Guest]: Not immediately, they're children.

01:27:24.680 --> 01:27:27.040
[Guest]: So in the beginning, they're allowed to play hopscotch with each other and play board games

01:27:27.040 --> 01:27:29.000
[Guest]: and things like that for one hour every day.

01:27:29.000 --> 01:27:30.000
[Guest]: Nothing more than that.

01:27:30.000 --> 01:27:31.000
[Guest]: There's no contact beyond that.

01:27:31.000 --> 01:27:34.920
[Guest]: Junior Rani's husband, unfortunately, is not, he's already a grown man when they marry.

01:27:34.920 --> 01:27:39.120
[Guest]: So by the time she's 14 and ready to consummate the marriage, he's in his mid 20s.

01:27:39.120 --> 01:27:41.280
[Guest]: He's got a graduate degree, but he's extremely orthodox.

01:27:41.280 --> 01:27:45.240
[Guest]: So just as she's unorthodox and rebellious, and she'll even play golf when she's pregnant

01:27:45.240 --> 01:27:48.080
[Guest]: and go out riding and learn to drive and things like that.

01:27:48.080 --> 01:27:51.240
[Guest]: This man won't shake hands with women thinking it's you know, I'm impure.

01:27:51.240 --> 01:27:54.640
[Guest]: At banquets, he'll sit there clutching a lemon because eating meat and eating in the presence

01:27:54.640 --> 01:27:56.240
[Guest]: of white people will make him lose his cast.

01:27:56.240 --> 01:27:59.760
[Amit Varma]: I actually highlighted that line in the book because it's such a fantastic detail that

01:27:59.760 --> 01:28:03.840
[Amit Varma]: at banquets, he's sitting holding a lemon because lemons absorbed impurities from.

01:28:03.840 --> 01:28:06.080
[Amit Varma]: Oh, that's the reason you're holding a lemon.

01:28:06.080 --> 01:28:07.080
[Amit Varma]: It's the same principle.

01:28:07.080 --> 01:28:10.600
[Guest]: You hang a lemon outside the door because it absorbs all the evil in the room.

01:28:10.600 --> 01:28:13.840
[Guest]: So naturally, the Junior Rani's guests were not pleased when she was there.

01:28:13.840 --> 01:28:16.840
[Guest]: And she's hosting a party and her husband sits there pretending they're all unwelcome,

01:28:16.840 --> 01:28:17.840
[Guest]: impure guests.

01:28:17.840 --> 01:28:21.960
[Guest]: And she was a shrewd, a very, very clever woman, for example, she was a vegetarian.

01:28:21.960 --> 01:28:25.880
[Guest]: So there are these wonderful stories about how, you know, garden parties that have fish

01:28:25.880 --> 01:28:29.880
[Guest]: fry going around with toothpicks, etc, for people to eat them.

01:28:29.880 --> 01:28:32.760
[Guest]: Now she couldn't offend her guests, but she was a vegetarian, so she couldn't eat the

01:28:32.760 --> 01:28:33.760
[Guest]: fish.

01:28:33.760 --> 01:28:37.440
[Guest]: So she would have tapioca or cassava cut in the exact shape and fried in the exact same

01:28:37.440 --> 01:28:38.440
[Guest]: fashion.

01:28:38.440 --> 01:28:39.440
[Guest]: And that would come to her on a tray.

01:28:39.440 --> 01:28:42.920
[Guest]: So she could eat something that looked like fish, but it was actually vegetarian, while

01:28:42.920 --> 01:28:46.080
[Guest]: her guests ate the actual fish while her husband sat there clutching a lemon.

01:28:46.080 --> 01:28:49.040
[Guest]: So it's as complicated as that.

01:28:49.040 --> 01:28:51.080
[Guest]: So Junior Rani's marriage is not very happy.

01:28:51.080 --> 01:28:55.600
[Guest]: Now the coming of the husbands add new complications to this because in the matrilineal system,

01:28:55.600 --> 01:28:57.000
[Guest]: the sisters are supposed to be tight.

01:28:57.000 --> 01:29:00.960
[Guest]: Now, to begin with, their mothers have a politics, so the sisters, these adopted Rani's don't

01:29:00.960 --> 01:29:01.960
[Guest]: get along.

01:29:01.960 --> 01:29:03.400
[Guest]: Senior and Junior Rani don't get along.

01:29:03.400 --> 01:29:07.480
[Guest]: The husbands come in, which means a new element comes in succession, who produces the next

01:29:07.480 --> 01:29:08.480
[Guest]: heir to the throne.

01:29:08.480 --> 01:29:11.800
[Guest]: They've been adopted to produce the next Maharaja, you know.

01:29:11.800 --> 01:29:15.240
[Amit Varma]: And the thing to notice, because all these people died, you know, you basically got a

01:29:15.240 --> 01:29:19.920
[Amit Varma]: king who's passing 50, all his predecessor kings have died before 50.

01:29:19.920 --> 01:29:25.160
[Amit Varma]: So he is like, I need an heir now, these kids have to produce heirs right away.

01:29:25.160 --> 01:29:29.600
[Amit Varma]: And the first son born out of either of these two girls is the next ruler, is the next ruler.

01:29:29.600 --> 01:29:31.640
[Amit Varma]: So now there is competition among them.

01:29:31.640 --> 01:29:34.680
[Amit Varma]: And you know, Sethu Lakshmibai has a head start of a year.

01:29:34.680 --> 01:29:38.440
[Amit Varma]: She gets married at 10, the other kid gets married, you know, around the same time, and

01:29:38.440 --> 01:29:41.240
[Guest]: then they turn 14 and the marriages are consummated.

01:29:41.240 --> 01:29:44.720
[Guest]: So Sethu Lakshmibai incidentally does get pregnant.

01:29:44.720 --> 01:29:48.560
[Guest]: But in the eighth month, the baby I think dies in the womb or something.

01:29:48.560 --> 01:29:49.920
[Guest]: And essentially, it's a stillbirth.

01:29:49.920 --> 01:29:52.120
[Guest]: It is alleged that there is black magic involved.

01:29:52.120 --> 01:29:53.880
[Guest]: There are stories, but no evidence of that.

01:29:53.880 --> 01:29:57.560
[Guest]: But it's a court, royal courts are full of rumors and factions and things like that.

01:29:57.560 --> 01:30:00.560
[Guest]: And once succession comes in, again, the mothers get involved.

01:30:00.560 --> 01:30:03.280
[Guest]: Because see, the junior Rani's mother has always been in the shadow of her sister and

01:30:03.280 --> 01:30:05.580
[Guest]: her daughter, the junior Rani is also junior.

01:30:05.580 --> 01:30:10.720
[Guest]: So now what happens is in 1912, at the age of 16, the junior Rani produces a male heir.

01:30:10.720 --> 01:30:13.720
[Guest]: Suddenly, this becomes in many ways her passport to prominence.

01:30:13.720 --> 01:30:17.880
[Guest]: From being in the shadow of her sister, the senior Rani, she is now mother to the heir

01:30:17.880 --> 01:30:18.880
[Guest]: apparent.

01:30:18.880 --> 01:30:22.880
[Guest]: So the heir apparent is entitled to his own palace, to his own servants, to his own income,

01:30:22.880 --> 01:30:23.880
[Guest]: etc.

01:30:23.880 --> 01:30:27.440
[Guest]: Even though the boy is just a baby, she says, as his mother, I should be able to manage

01:30:27.440 --> 01:30:28.440
[Guest]: that.

01:30:28.440 --> 01:30:29.440
[Guest]: And the Maharaja says that makes sense.

01:30:29.440 --> 01:30:33.200
[Guest]: He is, even though he's an infant, he's automatically heir apparent to the throne.

01:30:33.200 --> 01:30:36.080
[Guest]: So everything an heir apparent is entitled to, the junior Rani gets.

01:30:36.080 --> 01:30:38.400
[Guest]: So she moves out of the senior Rani's shadow.

01:30:38.400 --> 01:30:42.520
[Guest]: The senior Rani, meanwhile, feels that, you know, she's now suddenly lost all her prominence.

01:30:42.520 --> 01:30:46.120
[Guest]: Because not only did she have this stillbirth after that, she had several miscarriages.

01:30:46.120 --> 01:30:49.280
[Guest]: And then for the next nearly a decade, she doesn't have children.

01:30:49.280 --> 01:30:50.280
[Guest]: She's struggling to have children.

01:30:50.280 --> 01:30:51.520
[Guest]: And eventually she has girls.

01:30:51.520 --> 01:30:56.040
[Guest]: Whereas her sister produces the Maharaja, next Maharaja, she produces a girl to continue

01:30:56.040 --> 01:31:00.200
[Guest]: the matrilineal line and she produces a spear to the throne in the form of a second son.

01:31:00.200 --> 01:31:04.160
[Guest]: So she's performed her duty to the dynasty within a space of one decade.

01:31:04.160 --> 01:31:06.000
[Guest]: She's gone ahead and produced three children.

01:31:06.000 --> 01:31:07.000
[Guest]: Senior Rani has no children.

01:31:07.000 --> 01:31:11.080
[Guest]: She only has two daughters much later, after all the junior Rani's children are born.

01:31:11.080 --> 01:31:14.920
[Guest]: So this to begin with, things are getting a little lopsided in terms of who's the main

01:31:14.920 --> 01:31:16.640
[Guest]: figure in the family.

01:31:16.640 --> 01:31:18.760
[Amit Varma]: Then we come to the year 1920.

01:31:18.760 --> 01:31:22.160
[Amit Varma]: And what was also interesting are the details in your book about how after this first son

01:31:22.160 --> 01:31:27.680
[Amit Varma]: is born, she is so paranoid that he's going to be sabotaged and he's going to be killed

01:31:27.680 --> 01:31:33.960
[Amit Varma]: as allegedly earlier kings might have been, that she doesn't allow anyone to meet the

01:31:33.960 --> 01:31:34.960
[Amit Varma]: kid.

01:31:34.960 --> 01:31:35.960
[Amit Varma]: Have free access to the boy.

01:31:35.960 --> 01:31:39.640
[Amit Varma]: Including the senior Rani Lakshmibai's husband, the renowned scholar Kerala Varma, who is

01:31:39.640 --> 01:31:42.200
[Guest]: like a father figure to both these young girls.

01:31:42.200 --> 01:31:44.560
[Amit Varma]: Father of modern Malayalam prose literature.

01:31:44.560 --> 01:31:47.520
[Amit Varma]: And I want to come back to Sanskrit and Malayalam in a bit.

01:31:47.520 --> 01:31:51.240
[Amit Varma]: But he's so he's basically like a father figure to both these young girls.

01:31:51.240 --> 01:31:55.400
[Amit Varma]: And suddenly one of them gets a son and he's not allowed to be alone with the child.

01:31:55.400 --> 01:31:59.360
[Guest]: And ditto, of course, the aunt is like no any other kid is allowed because I mean, there

01:31:59.360 --> 01:32:00.360
[Guest]: are no rules.

01:32:00.360 --> 01:32:03.160
[Guest]: It's just that it's very clear that you are not welcome around this child because people

01:32:03.160 --> 01:32:04.160
[Guest]: are paranoid.

01:32:04.160 --> 01:32:08.760
[Guest]: Frankly, that he's not a boy again, that kid from day one is a future Maharaja.

01:32:08.760 --> 01:32:11.640
[Guest]: He is seen, therefore, as that icon.

01:32:11.640 --> 01:32:14.360
[Guest]: He's not seen, therefore, as a little boy, he's not a normal baby.

01:32:14.360 --> 01:32:18.720
[Amit Varma]: And he also he is also the relief for the baggage that these two women, junior Rani

01:32:18.720 --> 01:32:21.080
[Guest]: and her mother have carried for years and years and years.

01:32:21.080 --> 01:32:22.080
[Guest]: Yeah.

01:32:22.080 --> 01:32:23.080
[Guest]: That's the thing.

01:32:23.080 --> 01:32:25.800
[Guest]: A politics that starts with Ravi Varma's bad marriage.

01:32:25.800 --> 01:32:29.840
[Guest]: So husband and wife don't get along, their daughters that produces politics between their

01:32:29.840 --> 01:32:33.520
[Guest]: daughters in terms of the beautiful daughter who Ravi Varma paints and uses as a model

01:32:33.520 --> 01:32:36.680
[Guest]: and who's given, who's a de facto head of the family and the not so beautiful daughter

01:32:36.680 --> 01:32:37.680
[Amit Varma]: who's always in the shadows.

01:32:37.680 --> 01:32:38.680
[Amit Varma]: Who the mother liked apparently.

01:32:38.680 --> 01:32:39.680
[Guest]: Yeah.

01:32:39.680 --> 01:32:43.560
[Guest]: Then you have royal children who are now adopted into a royal family where power gets involved.

01:32:43.560 --> 01:32:47.880
[Guest]: So in addition to family dispute and the usual family quarrels that all families have powers

01:32:47.880 --> 01:32:48.880
[Guest]: involved now.

01:32:48.880 --> 01:32:49.880
[Guest]: So things start going.

01:32:49.880 --> 01:32:53.720
[Guest]: I mean, the standard of the scale of the problem starts increasing, magnifying.

01:32:53.720 --> 01:32:58.200
[Guest]: Now what happens is that Setulakshmi becomes cornered at court, partly also because she's

01:32:58.200 --> 01:33:03.640
[Guest]: extremely devoted to her husband and her uncle, the Maharaja, the old man, Mulam Dharam, does

01:33:03.640 --> 01:33:05.040
[Guest]: not like it.

01:33:05.040 --> 01:33:09.040
[Guest]: And he says, you know, this boy is just your consort, you should keep him in his place.

01:33:09.040 --> 01:33:12.800
[Guest]: And the consort, her husband, is also getting big airs about who he is in the sense that,

01:33:12.800 --> 01:33:14.840
[Guest]: you know, junior Rani is the junior Rani.

01:33:14.840 --> 01:33:17.000
[Guest]: She's junior to the senior Rani.

01:33:17.000 --> 01:33:19.360
[Guest]: But for the husband, she's still a queen.

01:33:19.360 --> 01:33:23.400
[Guest]: So he has to bow to the junior Rani also, because she is still royalty and he's not.

01:33:23.400 --> 01:33:24.400
[Guest]: He hates that.

01:33:24.400 --> 01:33:27.200
[Guest]: He feels that as husband to the senior Rani, why should he bow to the junior Rani?

01:33:27.200 --> 01:33:31.240
[Guest]: Whereas junior Rani says, whether or not I'm junior in my family is not your business.

01:33:31.240 --> 01:33:33.740
[Guest]: As far as you're concerned, I am also a Rani.

01:33:33.740 --> 01:33:34.840
[Guest]: So you have to bow to me.

01:33:34.840 --> 01:33:38.160
[Guest]: So the feud begins between these two people and the senior Rani supports her husband saying,

01:33:38.160 --> 01:33:39.920
[Guest]: you know, how dare you speak to my husband like this.

01:33:39.920 --> 01:33:42.160
[Guest]: She's being cornered because she can't produce children.

01:33:42.160 --> 01:33:43.480
[Guest]: All she has for support is her husband.

01:33:43.480 --> 01:33:45.640
[Guest]: So she becomes increasingly close to her husband.

01:33:45.640 --> 01:33:49.280
[Guest]: And junior Rani says, this is not your loyalty should be to the matrilineal family, not to

01:33:49.280 --> 01:33:50.280
[Guest]: your husband.

01:33:50.280 --> 01:33:53.160
[Guest]: This is also linked to that larger Victorian conversation that wives should be devoted

01:33:53.160 --> 01:33:56.760
[Guest]: to their husbands, matrilineal system is bad, patriarchal families are better.

01:33:56.760 --> 01:34:01.200
[Guest]: So this whole conversation is also part of that larger change in society.

01:34:01.200 --> 01:34:05.000
[Guest]: What is also interesting is the Maharaja at that time is this man called Moolam Tirtha,

01:34:05.000 --> 01:34:07.080
[Guest]: the uncle of these adopted Rani's.

01:34:07.080 --> 01:34:09.560
[Guest]: He is entirely a puppet in the hands of some courtiers.

01:34:09.560 --> 01:34:12.840
[Guest]: That is another fascinating story that tells you a lot about marriage and matrilineal in

01:34:12.840 --> 01:34:13.840
[Guest]: Kerala.

01:34:13.840 --> 01:34:15.780
[Guest]: So the Maharaja is married first to a lady.

01:34:15.780 --> 01:34:17.040
[Guest]: She dies, leaving him a son.

01:34:17.040 --> 01:34:20.100
[Guest]: He doesn't marry again for about 16-17 years.

01:34:20.100 --> 01:34:23.040
[Guest]: At some point, he falls in love with a lady called Kartiayani.

01:34:23.040 --> 01:34:28.680
[Guest]: Now Kartiayani is the wife of a palace servant and she belongs to a family who traditionally

01:34:28.680 --> 01:34:32.180
[Guest]: supplied women who husk the rice, etc. in the Padmanabhaswamy temple.

01:34:32.180 --> 01:34:37.680
[Guest]: So middle class Naya family, not aristocracy, not of especially high birth or anything.

01:34:37.680 --> 01:34:40.440
[Guest]: And she is married to a palace servant called Shangubalai.

01:34:40.440 --> 01:34:42.960
[Guest]: Now what happens is Maharaja falls in love with this married woman.

01:34:42.960 --> 01:34:44.920
[Guest]: Shangubalai agrees to give up his wife.

01:34:44.920 --> 01:34:45.920
[Guest]: Divorce is easy.

01:34:45.920 --> 01:34:47.600
[Guest]: So he divorces Kartiayani.

01:34:47.600 --> 01:34:49.280
[Guest]: Maharaja decides to marry Kartiayani.

01:34:49.280 --> 01:34:50.280
[Guest]: But there's a rule.

01:34:50.280 --> 01:34:54.520
[Guest]: Maharajas can only marry from specific, you know, families called Amma Vidus in Trivandrum,

01:34:54.520 --> 01:34:58.040
[Guest]: which are, you know, the families from which they take their brides usually.

01:34:58.040 --> 01:34:59.040
[Guest]: So what does he do?

01:34:59.040 --> 01:35:02.800
[Guest]: He adopts Kartiayani into one of these Amma Vidus, raises her status in society.

01:35:02.800 --> 01:35:06.000
[Guest]: She suddenly becomes an aristocratic woman through adoption and the Maharaja marries

01:35:06.000 --> 01:35:07.000
[Guest]: her.

01:35:07.000 --> 01:35:11.720
[Guest]: In return for, so now Maharaja is married to an already married woman.

01:35:11.720 --> 01:35:16.240
[Guest]: In return for giving her up, the ex-husband is also given the title of Tambi and raised

01:35:16.240 --> 01:35:18.500
[Guest]: into a very senior position in court.

01:35:18.500 --> 01:35:21.520
[Guest]: And he becomes the real controller of the Maharaja.

01:35:21.520 --> 01:35:25.280
[Guest]: Increasingly the Maharaja's access to the Maharaja, you know, a lot of decisions he

01:35:25.280 --> 01:35:28.720
[Guest]: takes are actually channeled through this man called Shankaran, Shangubalai becomes

01:35:28.720 --> 01:35:29.720
[Guest]: Shankaran Tambi.

01:35:29.720 --> 01:35:31.680
[Guest]: Through his second wife's first husband.

01:35:31.680 --> 01:35:35.680
[Guest]: So once in court, there was a, there was a journalist who was asked in court who is Shankaran

01:35:35.680 --> 01:35:36.680
[Guest]: Tambi.

01:35:36.680 --> 01:35:39.200
[Guest]: Shankaran Tambi was the former husband of the Maharaja's present wife, because that

01:35:39.200 --> 01:35:40.200
[Guest]: was the fact of it.

01:35:40.200 --> 01:35:42.880
[Guest]: I mean, it was the former husband of the Maharaja's present wife.

01:35:42.880 --> 01:35:46.800
[Guest]: So this coterie around the Maharaja, Sethu Lakshmivaya does not like, because she does

01:35:46.800 --> 01:35:48.400
[Guest]: not like the corruption they're involved in.

01:35:48.400 --> 01:35:50.200
[Guest]: She does not like the culture that's there.

01:35:50.200 --> 01:35:53.800
[Guest]: When she's a child, she can't object, but as soon as she turns 18, she and her husband

01:35:53.800 --> 01:35:55.200
[Guest]: start standing apart from each other.

01:35:55.200 --> 01:35:58.240
[Amit Varma]: And there's even a rumor, like you pointed out, that this former husband of the present

01:35:58.240 --> 01:36:00.840
[Amit Varma]: wife was behind the three deaths that happened.

01:36:00.840 --> 01:36:05.280
[Guest]: There was a rumor that he got those princes killed because they were in his way.

01:36:05.280 --> 01:36:07.520
[Guest]: They didn't support, they didn't approve of him.

01:36:07.520 --> 01:36:10.120
[Guest]: So he's essentially a shady character.

01:36:10.120 --> 01:36:15.040
[Guest]: So senior Rani is cornered, junior Rani becomes the main person, the mother of the new heir,

01:36:15.040 --> 01:36:16.040
[Guest]: etc.

01:36:16.040 --> 01:36:19.920
[Guest]: Then in 1924, the Maharaja, the reigning Maharaja dies in his 60s.

01:36:19.920 --> 01:36:23.520
[Guest]: This creates an awkward situation because junior Rani's son is only 12 years old.

01:36:23.520 --> 01:36:25.240
[Guest]: So he's not old enough to rule.

01:36:25.240 --> 01:36:29.520
[Guest]: In North Indian patriarchal kingdoms, usually the British would appoint the wife or the

01:36:29.520 --> 01:36:34.720
[Guest]: widow of the dead Maharaja as a regent, and they would appoint a pro-British regency council.

01:36:34.720 --> 01:36:37.520
[Guest]: And this is how the state would be governed till the boy grew up.

01:36:37.520 --> 01:36:41.200
[Guest]: And in the interim, the boy would be trained by Englishmen to be loyal to the British Empire

01:36:41.200 --> 01:36:42.200
[Guest]: and so on.

01:36:42.200 --> 01:36:43.200
[Guest]: Complete brainwashing would happen.

01:36:43.200 --> 01:36:47.540
[Guest]: In Travancore, however, because it was matrilineal, the law was very clear.

01:36:47.540 --> 01:36:51.640
[Guest]: If there is no male or if the existing male member is not in a capacity to rule either

01:36:51.640 --> 01:36:57.280
[Guest]: for minority or for being mentally incapable or whatever, it is the power to rule goes

01:36:57.280 --> 01:36:59.240
[Guest]: to the eldest female member.

01:36:59.240 --> 01:37:00.440
[Guest]: What does that translate into?

01:37:00.440 --> 01:37:05.040
[Guest]: Till the junior Rani's son comes of age, power vests with the senior Rani.

01:37:05.040 --> 01:37:09.520
[Guest]: So for junior Rani's son, what she suddenly discovers is her sister is going to rule,

01:37:09.520 --> 01:37:10.520
[Guest]: not her.

01:37:10.520 --> 01:37:12.720
[Guest]: So first she says there should be a council and she should be a member.

01:37:12.720 --> 01:37:13.720
[Guest]: Senior Rani says no.

01:37:13.720 --> 01:37:15.560
[Guest]: There have been regents in the past in Travancore.

01:37:15.560 --> 01:37:18.020
[Guest]: In fact, the word regent is a British invention.

01:37:18.020 --> 01:37:20.980
[Guest]: In the matrilineal system, when a woman rules, she rules as Maharaja.

01:37:20.980 --> 01:37:24.880
[Guest]: So in Malayalam documents, Sethulakshmi Bai is called Puraadam Tirunel Maharaja, not Maharani.

01:37:24.880 --> 01:37:28.040
[Guest]: Colloquially, she's Maharani, but she's also a Maharaja when she rules.

01:37:28.040 --> 01:37:29.040
[Guest]: And that means she has full powers.

01:37:29.040 --> 01:37:31.640
[Guest]: There's no regency council put by the British.

01:37:31.640 --> 01:37:35.080
[Guest]: She rules directly with the minister like all other rulers before her.

01:37:35.080 --> 01:37:39.600
[Guest]: This now makes that power conflict between the sisters more direct because suddenly senior

01:37:39.600 --> 01:37:41.340
[Guest]: Rani is in power for the junior son.

01:37:41.340 --> 01:37:44.360
[Guest]: So the next seven years, senior is in control and the junior is waiting.

01:37:44.360 --> 01:37:46.680
[Guest]: She's dying to sort of get her son in power.

01:37:46.680 --> 01:37:49.840
[Guest]: And she eventually manages to persuade Lord Willingdon, who's the viceroy, to reduce the

01:37:49.840 --> 01:37:53.440
[Guest]: regency by six months and get her son installed.

01:37:53.440 --> 01:37:58.660
[Guest]: After which, you know, the feud between the sisters really does escalate in many ways.

01:37:58.660 --> 01:38:02.400
[Amit Varma]: And what is interesting here is that you'd imagine that, okay, this young shy girl who

01:38:02.400 --> 01:38:05.560
[Amit Varma]: is, you know, not very outgoing, you don't really know what she thinks.

01:38:05.560 --> 01:38:07.880
[Amit Varma]: She is now the Maharaja, as it were.

01:38:07.880 --> 01:38:13.720
[Amit Varma]: And she will just let, you know, her officers and whatever do their thing, or a husband

01:38:13.720 --> 01:38:15.640
[Amit Varma]: do their thing and take a backseat.

01:38:15.640 --> 01:38:20.400
[Amit Varma]: But no, this lady turns out to be extremely formidable and a significant early sign of

01:38:20.400 --> 01:38:22.880
[Amit Varma]: this being the Vycombe rebel, you know, rebel.

01:38:22.880 --> 01:38:27.280
[Guest]: In fact, when she comes to power, the then British resident in a confidential document

01:38:27.280 --> 01:38:31.680
[Guest]: to the viceroy describes her as the pious orthodox domestic type, by which basically

01:38:31.680 --> 01:38:33.120
[Guest]: he means she's a housewife.

01:38:33.120 --> 01:38:34.120
[Guest]: She's not really going to rule.

01:38:34.120 --> 01:38:35.520
[Guest]: Her husband is probably going to control her.

01:38:35.520 --> 01:38:39.520
[Guest]: And that's how the government will be conducted until the Maharaja comes of age.

01:38:39.520 --> 01:38:41.880
[Guest]: What they discover is no, she's actually got a mind of her own.

01:38:41.880 --> 01:38:42.880
[Guest]: She is gentle.

01:38:42.880 --> 01:38:43.880
[Guest]: She is shy.

01:38:43.880 --> 01:38:44.880
[Guest]: She doesn't like the limelight.

01:38:44.880 --> 01:38:45.880
[Guest]: But she's also exceedingly hardworking.

01:38:45.880 --> 01:38:47.840
[Guest]: I mean, part of it is not surprising.

01:38:47.840 --> 01:38:50.280
[Guest]: The fact is, she's been cornered for the last decade in court.

01:38:50.280 --> 01:38:51.280
[Guest]: She's had no status.

01:38:51.280 --> 01:38:52.500
[Guest]: So she has something to prove.

01:38:52.500 --> 01:38:55.000
[Guest]: She knows that she's not going to hold power forever.

01:38:55.000 --> 01:38:57.800
[Guest]: She's only going to hold it for a period of about seven to eight years.

01:38:57.800 --> 01:39:01.380
[Guest]: And in that time, she somehow has to prove herself, she has to do her best.

01:39:01.380 --> 01:39:05.840
[Guest]: And she and her husband have this joint pact that they're going to work as hard as possible

01:39:05.840 --> 01:39:09.600
[Guest]: and try and get, you know, carve out their place in history because they know otherwise

01:39:09.600 --> 01:39:13.400
[Guest]: once the junior Rani's son comes to power, they're going to be shunted back into the

01:39:13.400 --> 01:39:14.400
[Amit Varma]: corner.

01:39:14.400 --> 01:39:17.120
[Guest]: They're not really going to enjoy any influence after that.

01:39:17.120 --> 01:39:19.840
[Guest]: So those seven years become very important for them.

01:39:19.840 --> 01:39:24.200
[Guest]: And there is at that time, this Vycombe Satyagraha going on, which is to open up all roads around

01:39:24.200 --> 01:39:27.000
[Guest]: the temple in Vycombe to Dalits as well.

01:39:27.000 --> 01:39:29.440
[Guest]: Because till then, Dalits were not allowed on the spot.

01:39:29.440 --> 01:39:32.800
[Guest]: And this is, there's a major agitation going on in the middle, there are floods in Kerala

01:39:32.800 --> 01:39:37.240
[Guest]: like the recent floods we had in 2019 and 2018, chaos happening.

01:39:37.240 --> 01:39:41.240
[Guest]: And this woman's coming to rule, a woman everybody thinks is a housewife has now suddenly been

01:39:41.240 --> 01:39:43.120
[Guest]: placed in a position of ruling.

01:39:43.120 --> 01:39:46.620
[Guest]: She however, breaks a lot of these notions about her.

01:39:46.620 --> 01:39:49.680
[Guest]: She invites delegates to come and meet her, representatives of both sides.

01:39:49.680 --> 01:39:50.760
[Guest]: She listens to her officials.

01:39:50.760 --> 01:39:53.640
[Guest]: She listens to these people and she comes up with a compromise solution.

01:39:53.640 --> 01:39:54.640
[Guest]: She meets with Gandhiji.

01:39:54.640 --> 01:39:59.480
[Guest]: Gandhiji comes to, you know, talk to her and he's stunned because he comes to meet her

01:39:59.480 --> 01:40:01.440
[Guest]: not in the palace because she moves around a lot.

01:40:01.440 --> 01:40:05.320
[Guest]: She prefers staying in these little travelers' bungalows in different parts of the state.

01:40:05.320 --> 01:40:09.320
[Guest]: So when Gandhiji comes, she's staying in a beach bungalow next to, in a guest house at

01:40:09.320 --> 01:40:10.600
[Guest]: Varkala beach.

01:40:10.600 --> 01:40:14.160
[Guest]: And he's stunned because he walks in and the story in the family goes that he thought that

01:40:14.160 --> 01:40:17.840
[Guest]: she was her lady-in-waiting or something because he walks into a room and all he sees is this

01:40:17.840 --> 01:40:21.700
[Guest]: woman dressed in plain white, no ornaments, like just a single chain around her neck and

01:40:21.700 --> 01:40:23.400
[Guest]: standing in the room with her husband.

01:40:23.400 --> 01:40:26.760
[Guest]: And Gandhiji thought that a princess or a queen or a Maharani would be in silks and

01:40:26.760 --> 01:40:28.800
[Guest]: wearing pearls and diamonds and things like that.

01:40:28.800 --> 01:40:32.720
[Guest]: And he wrote in his journal, in his magazine called Young India, that he walked in expecting

01:40:32.720 --> 01:40:33.720
[Guest]: something like that.

01:40:33.720 --> 01:40:37.960
[Guest]: But what he saw was this highly simple woman who should be a lesson to other Indian princes,

01:40:37.960 --> 01:40:41.920
[Guest]: not only in simplicity, but also in how she behaves and her sort of perspective and her

01:40:41.920 --> 01:40:42.920
[Guest]: views and so on.

01:40:42.920 --> 01:40:47.240
[Guest]: And she hammers out a deal with Gandhiji saying that she's not going to bulldoze anything

01:40:47.240 --> 01:40:48.240
[Guest]: through.

01:40:48.240 --> 01:40:51.720
[Guest]: She says reform, you have to persuade people, win them over and through consensus is the

01:40:51.720 --> 01:40:53.220
[Guest]: way she's going to work.

01:40:53.220 --> 01:40:56.600
[Guest]: So she says fine, they want access to the roads, she'll give them access to three roads

01:40:56.600 --> 01:40:57.600
[Guest]: around the temple.

01:40:57.600 --> 01:40:58.600
[Guest]: There are four roads, right?

01:40:58.600 --> 01:41:01.400
[Guest]: All four sides of the temple, take access to the three roads.

01:41:01.400 --> 01:41:04.920
[Guest]: The fourth road, which is considered the main entrance and the Brahmins are all objecting

01:41:04.920 --> 01:41:08.280
[Guest]: saying lower caste people should not be allowed, she said for the time being, let that be in

01:41:08.280 --> 01:41:11.880
[Guest]: the hands of the Brahmins and she constructs a parallel road and she says this is open

01:41:11.880 --> 01:41:14.400
[Guest]: to everybody irrespective of caste.

01:41:14.400 --> 01:41:18.280
[Guest]: And slowly over the next four or five years, practically on a case-by-case basis based

01:41:18.280 --> 01:41:22.280
[Guest]: on issues in different temples, she starts opening up public roads to all castes till

01:41:22.280 --> 01:41:27.200
[Guest]: by 1929, basically all roads are thrown open to people of all castes.

01:41:27.200 --> 01:41:30.520
[Guest]: And this is what sets the stage for something her successor does, which is to throw open

01:41:30.520 --> 01:41:33.140
[Guest]: temples itself in the mid 1930s.

01:41:33.140 --> 01:41:36.520
[Guest]: She sorts of builds up that process and allows that to happen.

01:41:36.520 --> 01:41:40.920
[Guest]: She appoints as one of the first things she does when she's put in power, when she inherits

01:41:40.920 --> 01:41:45.480
[Guest]: power from her uncle is to place a woman at the head of the medical department.

01:41:45.480 --> 01:41:47.600
[Guest]: That was essentially like the health minister at the time.

01:41:47.600 --> 01:41:48.640
[Guest]: She gets a woman in that position.

01:41:48.640 --> 01:41:52.600
[Guest]: She starts nominating women to the Legislative Council of Travancore, a second representative

01:41:52.600 --> 01:41:55.520
[Guest]: house there also she nominates women.

01:41:55.520 --> 01:42:00.040
[Guest]: The first feature film that comes out of Kerala has a Dalit woman playing an upper caste lady

01:42:00.040 --> 01:42:01.040
[Guest]: and her life is threatened.

01:42:01.040 --> 01:42:04.840
[Guest]: All these men say, how dare a Dalit woman play upper caste roles.

01:42:04.840 --> 01:42:09.560
[Guest]: This woman, the Marani gives her protection and actually ensures that she's kept safe.

01:42:09.560 --> 01:42:13.800
[Guest]: There's midwives, she opens up very simple stuff, but stuff that has major repercussions

01:42:13.800 --> 01:42:14.840
[Guest]: for women.

01:42:14.840 --> 01:42:20.680
[Guest]: So, births, midwife classes are introduced, batches of midwives are trained and by the

01:42:20.680 --> 01:42:24.240
[Guest]: end of her reign, one-fifth of all the births in Travancore are handled in a professional

01:42:24.240 --> 01:42:27.560
[Guest]: manner even in villages because these midwives are sent out even to rural areas.

01:42:27.560 --> 01:42:29.600
[Guest]: And this is something which would never strike a male Maharaja.

01:42:29.600 --> 01:42:33.040
[Guest]: Yeah, because it's not really a thing for them.

01:42:33.040 --> 01:42:35.280
[Guest]: But it's not like she focused only on health and women.

01:42:35.280 --> 01:42:36.600
[Guest]: She also focused on public works.

01:42:36.600 --> 01:42:39.640
[Guest]: Some of the biggest roads and highways and bridges that are still being used in Kerala

01:42:39.640 --> 01:42:40.920
[Guest]: were built by her.

01:42:40.920 --> 01:42:45.040
[Guest]: She allocated one-fifth of her revenues to public works and one-fifth of her revenues

01:42:45.040 --> 01:42:48.760
[Guest]: to education, which meant there was a huge boost in school building and running schools,

01:42:48.760 --> 01:42:49.760
[Guest]: including private schools.

01:42:49.760 --> 01:42:53.000
[Guest]: She starts, in a major way, giving a lot of grants to even private schools so that they

01:42:53.000 --> 01:42:54.000
[Guest]: can match up.

01:42:54.000 --> 01:42:55.000
[Guest]: Textbook development, etc.

01:42:55.000 --> 01:42:59.880
[Guest]: Schools that, you know, don't have enough material, she'll send them from the capital.

01:42:59.880 --> 01:43:01.920
[Guest]: Public works, you know, Cochin Harbour.

01:43:01.920 --> 01:43:06.360
[Guest]: Cochin became again a port of significance because she tied up with the Cochin Maharaja.

01:43:06.360 --> 01:43:09.920
[Guest]: Cochin's not technically in her control, but she invested in it because she knew her state

01:43:09.920 --> 01:43:10.920
[Amit Varma]: would also benefit.

01:43:10.920 --> 01:43:14.880
[Amit Varma]: In fact, you've described that at length, and that kind of struck me because it shows

01:43:14.880 --> 01:43:18.840
[Amit Varma]: an instinctive understanding, not just of the positive externalities of public goods

01:43:18.840 --> 01:43:20.560
[Amit Varma]: like a port like that.

01:43:20.560 --> 01:43:25.080
[Amit Varma]: She's actually spending money of her own kingdom on what belongs to another kingdom.

01:43:25.080 --> 01:43:29.440
[Amit Varma]: Because like you said, Cochin is separate and the British have control.

01:43:29.440 --> 01:43:33.520
[Amit Varma]: And you know, to not be stuck in a zero-sum mentality, to be able to understand that this

01:43:33.520 --> 01:43:36.960
[Amit Varma]: will benefit us also seems remarkably forward.

01:43:36.960 --> 01:43:40.240
[Amit Varma]: Another thing that struck me going back to her meeting with Gandhi was, two things struck

01:43:40.240 --> 01:43:43.200
[Amit Varma]: me from that, like when he goes there to negotiate with her.

01:43:43.200 --> 01:43:47.760
[Amit Varma]: One, as you describe, is that as he's leaving, she says, I hope before you leave Kerala,

01:43:47.760 --> 01:43:49.360
[Amit Varma]: you'll meet the other Mahatma.

01:43:49.360 --> 01:43:53.920
[Amit Varma]: And this other Mahatma she's referring to is Narayana Guru, who's actually from a lower

01:43:53.920 --> 01:43:54.920
[Amit Varma]: caste.

01:43:54.920 --> 01:43:59.840
[Amit Varma]: So it is almost astonishing that a Maharaja of a higher caste is, you know, referring

01:43:59.840 --> 01:44:00.840
[Guest]: to a person.

01:44:00.840 --> 01:44:02.160
[Guest]: And she never met him personally.

01:44:02.160 --> 01:44:03.160
[Guest]: She never met him.

01:44:03.160 --> 01:44:04.160
[Guest]: She knew his significance.

01:44:04.160 --> 01:44:07.400
[Guest]: The thing is, what is interesting about her is, it's very difficult to place her in an

01:44:07.400 --> 01:44:11.400
[Guest]: exact box, because she's not a feminist in the sense, like the junior Rani, she didn't

01:44:11.400 --> 01:44:14.880
[Guest]: get a birth control activist at Trivandrum, but she's a feminist in the sense as J. Devika,

01:44:14.880 --> 01:44:18.600
[Guest]: the feminist scholar in Trivandrum was telling me, when I interviewed her for the book, she

01:44:18.600 --> 01:44:20.200
[Guest]: created spaces for women.

01:44:20.200 --> 01:44:21.560
[Guest]: She didn't promote individual women.

01:44:21.560 --> 01:44:26.480
[Guest]: She created spaces by putting aside seats for women in the legislative council, by allowing

01:44:26.480 --> 01:44:30.560
[Guest]: women to go and study law, by giving scholarships for women to go to medical school, you know,

01:44:30.560 --> 01:44:31.720
[Guest]: these programs that she started.

01:44:31.720 --> 01:44:36.200
[Guest]: She started this very innovative scheme, where any girl in Travancore who went to college

01:44:36.200 --> 01:44:40.080
[Guest]: was invited automatically to tea at the palace with the Maharani, just as a sort of incentive

01:44:40.080 --> 01:44:41.720
[Guest]: saying that, you know, you can get access.

01:44:41.720 --> 01:44:43.240
[Guest]: She was the chief celebrity of her time.

01:44:43.240 --> 01:44:46.240
[Guest]: So this was a way of, you know, inspiring girls to actually go out of that.

01:44:46.240 --> 01:44:47.240
[Amit Varma]: She was Kim Kardashian in the palace.

01:44:47.240 --> 01:44:50.240
[Guest]: Well, I wouldn't use that analogy.

01:44:50.240 --> 01:44:54.160
[Guest]: So she was, you know, she had innovative ways of promoting what she wanted.

01:44:54.160 --> 01:44:56.880
[Guest]: So it was public works, but on a social level.

01:44:56.880 --> 01:45:01.000
[Guest]: Look, the 1920s were a time of economic boom, till the Great Depression happens in 29.

01:45:01.000 --> 01:45:03.440
[Guest]: There's a huge boom around the world.

01:45:03.440 --> 01:45:07.840
[Guest]: She realizes that who are the engines of the economy in terms of trade and enterprise,

01:45:07.840 --> 01:45:11.640
[Guest]: the Nayas and the Brahmins, the upper castes are landed communities, land is sinking, agriculture

01:45:11.640 --> 01:45:15.040
[Guest]: is not the future, trade and business and factories, and these are the things that are

01:45:15.040 --> 01:45:16.040
[Guest]: the future.

01:45:16.040 --> 01:45:17.560
[Guest]: The communities that are doing this are who?

01:45:17.560 --> 01:45:20.840
[Guest]: Syrian Christians, who are in a privileged community, and the Eidavas.

01:45:20.840 --> 01:45:25.560
[Guest]: Now, the Eidavas were a low caste community that cultivated palm trees and toddy tappers,

01:45:25.560 --> 01:45:26.560
[Guest]: etc.

01:45:26.560 --> 01:45:27.560
[Guest]: But they also worked in Koya.

01:45:27.560 --> 01:45:31.280
[Guest]: Now, earlier, they would produce Koya for local markets, their feudal lords, etc.

01:45:31.280 --> 01:45:34.680
[Guest]: The colonial economy connected Travancore to the colonial ecosystem.

01:45:34.680 --> 01:45:38.320
[Guest]: So suddenly their Koya mats and carpets and ropes were in high demand in England and in

01:45:38.320 --> 01:45:40.880
[Guest]: Europe and different parts of the world in America.

01:45:40.880 --> 01:45:45.080
[Guest]: Suddenly the Eidava community started getting, instead of being paid in kind for their services,

01:45:45.080 --> 01:45:46.620
[Guest]: they started earning cash.

01:45:46.620 --> 01:45:49.960
[Guest]: With cash, they started buying land, their enterprises grew, the whole community started

01:45:49.960 --> 01:45:54.120
[Guest]: rising and a guru like Shri Narayana Guru gave it moral force, gave as a reformer and

01:45:54.120 --> 01:45:57.760
[Guest]: as a man who stood up for their rights and said that you don't need the approval of the

01:45:57.760 --> 01:45:58.760
[Guest]: upper castes.

01:45:58.760 --> 01:46:00.040
[Guest]: He gave it moral force.

01:46:00.040 --> 01:46:04.480
[Guest]: So by the 1920s, they became exceedingly powerful, even though they were technically a lower

01:46:04.480 --> 01:46:05.480
[Guest]: caste.

01:46:05.480 --> 01:46:06.480
[Guest]: Sethu Lakshmivaya recognized that.

01:46:06.480 --> 01:46:10.520
[Guest]: She realized that the Syrian Christians and the Eidavas are the engines of growth.

01:46:10.520 --> 01:46:14.040
[Guest]: She decided to promote these communities a great deal, much to the resentment of the

01:46:14.040 --> 01:46:15.620
[Guest]: old feudal communities.

01:46:15.620 --> 01:46:16.620
[Guest]: It's never easy.

01:46:16.620 --> 01:46:19.800
[Guest]: I mean, think of places in India, there are places in Uttar Pradesh, even now, still caught

01:46:19.800 --> 01:46:21.400
[Guest]: up in this feudal mentality.

01:46:21.400 --> 01:46:25.520
[Guest]: So think of the 1920s in a highly caste based society like Kerala, a woman coming in and

01:46:25.520 --> 01:46:29.320
[Guest]: promoting a lower caste and a Christian group, she appoints a Christian as her chief secretary,

01:46:29.320 --> 01:46:31.600
[Guest]: she appoints a Christian as her chief minister.

01:46:31.600 --> 01:46:35.480
[Guest]: It was I think the second time in Trivandrum's history that a Christian was made chief minister.

01:46:35.480 --> 01:46:38.180
[Guest]: The first time was when the state didn't have much of a choice and the British resident

01:46:38.180 --> 01:46:39.920
[Guest]: himself became the minister.

01:46:39.920 --> 01:46:42.480
[Guest]: But this was the first time she actually appoints a Christian to that position.

01:46:42.480 --> 01:46:47.880
[Guest]: So she had guts to do a lot of things of that nature, but she personally remained extremely

01:46:47.880 --> 01:46:48.880
[Guest]: conservative.

01:46:48.880 --> 01:46:53.280
[Guest]: There are amusing things like this, for example, when she came to power, both the British resident

01:46:53.280 --> 01:46:56.600
[Guest]: and the man she chose as her chief minister, a man called Mr. Watts, both of these men

01:46:56.600 --> 01:46:58.160
[Guest]: are in their 50s and they're both bachelors.

01:46:58.160 --> 01:47:02.640
[Guest]: Sethu Rakshabhai says, no, no, no, I can't receive bachelors in the palace.

01:47:02.640 --> 01:47:06.440
[Guest]: I can't be seen sitting and having conversations with unmarried men because she's orthodox.

01:47:06.440 --> 01:47:08.320
[Guest]: What will people think about me?

01:47:08.320 --> 01:47:12.080
[Guest]: So these poor men and middle-aged men are forced to go and marry women who are 20-30

01:47:12.080 --> 01:47:15.600
[Guest]: years younger than them, simply because the Maharani insists that they would get married.

01:47:15.600 --> 01:47:19.880
[Guest]: At the resident's wedding, she even sends a nice present saying that, you know, congratulations

01:47:19.880 --> 01:47:20.880
[Guest]: on your wedding.

01:47:20.880 --> 01:47:25.200
[Guest]: And the marriages are disasters because both are married highly younger, far younger women

01:47:25.200 --> 01:47:29.360
[Guest]: than they should have and, you know, the marriages are disasters for them, but they had no option

01:47:29.360 --> 01:47:32.640
[Guest]: but to get married because the Maharani of Travancore would not receive them in her drawing

01:47:32.640 --> 01:47:34.000
[Guest]: room otherwise.

01:47:34.000 --> 01:47:36.760
[Guest]: Every time she received them, she would make sure her husband was present.

01:47:36.760 --> 01:47:40.240
[Guest]: Her enemies used this to say that she was not controlled by the husband and he's there

01:47:40.240 --> 01:47:44.360
[Guest]: like this sort of conspiring weird influence behind her throne.

01:47:44.360 --> 01:47:49.160
[Guest]: And the fact was that, you know, she said nobody should gossip about me having any contact

01:47:49.160 --> 01:47:52.480
[Guest]: with unmarried men or any men face to face in a closed room.

01:47:52.480 --> 01:47:53.880
[Guest]: So my husband will always be there.

01:47:53.880 --> 01:47:57.040
[Guest]: And when a husband went hunting or shooting or whatever, she wouldn't meet the Diwan.

01:47:57.040 --> 01:47:59.960
[Guest]: It would be difficult for them to get meetings with her because she would not meet face to

01:47:59.960 --> 01:48:00.960
[Guest]: face with them.

01:48:00.960 --> 01:48:04.160
[Guest]: She would correspond and write letters and do it through notes and files, but not in

01:48:04.160 --> 01:48:05.160
[Guest]: person.

01:48:05.160 --> 01:48:09.520
[Guest]: So personally, very conservative, but in terms of her policies, creating lots of spaces for

01:48:09.520 --> 01:48:10.520
[Amit Varma]: women to grow.

01:48:10.520 --> 01:48:14.600
[Amit Varma]: In fact, what struck me about her governance was that the way I would sum it up and tell

01:48:14.600 --> 01:48:18.080
[Amit Varma]: me if you agree is that she was liberal, but not radical.

01:48:18.080 --> 01:48:21.920
[Amit Varma]: And an illustration of that being again going back to her meeting with Gandhi when she meets

01:48:21.920 --> 01:48:26.440
[Amit Varma]: him and she gives him the permission to make a statement about her feelings and the statement

01:48:26.440 --> 01:48:31.960
[Amit Varma]: he makes basically says that, you know, that she isn't against, you know, this caste entry

01:48:31.960 --> 01:48:33.880
[Amit Varma]: into temples and all of that.

01:48:33.880 --> 01:48:38.440
[Amit Varma]: But she is stuck in an entrance system where she cannot force it through herself.

01:48:38.440 --> 01:48:43.200
[Amit Varma]: But if public opinion is changed, then she can make it happen.

01:48:43.200 --> 01:48:47.600
[Amit Varma]: So she is not like a radical, she's not trying to force change through, she knows that things

01:48:47.600 --> 01:48:48.600
[Guest]: will take time.

01:48:48.600 --> 01:48:50.560
[Guest]: She's all about consensus and compromise.

01:48:50.560 --> 01:48:55.080
[Guest]: She's all about, you know, working slowly rather than leaping with great radical enthusiasm

01:48:55.080 --> 01:48:57.240
[Guest]: because she somehow has a distrust of it.

01:48:57.240 --> 01:48:59.120
[Guest]: She's always very cautious about what she does.

01:48:59.120 --> 01:49:03.120
[Guest]: But the result is that these seven years that she's in power become a huge boom in Travancore

01:49:03.120 --> 01:49:06.880
[Guest]: because revenues rise, a port is being built, the railways come to Trivandrum, electricity

01:49:06.880 --> 01:49:10.400
[Guest]: comes to Trivandrum, telephone services are expanded and open to the public.

01:49:10.400 --> 01:49:13.400
[Guest]: Things that are only available in the palace are now open to everybody, girls start going

01:49:13.400 --> 01:49:18.120
[Guest]: to medical school and there are major incentives for that, film industry becomes a reality

01:49:18.120 --> 01:49:23.720
[Guest]: in Travancore slowly with that first film that she supports, you know, so all kinds

01:49:23.720 --> 01:49:25.080
[Guest]: of developments are happening.

01:49:25.080 --> 01:49:29.440
[Guest]: Of course, in the palace, things are also going bad in the sense that her sister is

01:49:29.440 --> 01:49:32.640
[Guest]: completely chafing under this regime of the senior Rani.

01:49:32.640 --> 01:49:37.200
[Guest]: The junior Rani hates the fact that she has to live for so many years under her sister's

01:49:37.200 --> 01:49:38.200
[Guest]: thumb.

01:49:38.200 --> 01:49:41.000
[Guest]: So there's feuds over how much money should be given to her.

01:49:41.000 --> 01:49:44.040
[Guest]: So senior Rani says, your palace expenses, you decide how you want to spend it, those

01:49:44.040 --> 01:49:45.320
[Guest]: expenses I'll give.

01:49:45.320 --> 01:49:48.560
[Guest]: But junior Rani also wants more money, like she thinks anything connected with the future

01:49:48.560 --> 01:49:50.240
[Guest]: Maharaja, she should be allowed to control.

01:49:50.240 --> 01:49:53.960
[Guest]: But senior says, no, as the head of the matrilineal family, I am the eldest member, I will control

01:49:53.960 --> 01:49:54.960
[Guest]: those aspects.

01:49:54.960 --> 01:49:56.240
[Guest]: That is my privilege and prerogative.

01:49:56.240 --> 01:49:57.240
[Guest]: And it is true.

01:49:57.240 --> 01:49:58.840
[Guest]: But senior Rani takes it very personally.

01:49:58.840 --> 01:50:01.880
[Guest]: At one point, there's a black magic incident, you know, where they're trying to tell that

01:50:01.880 --> 01:50:02.880
[Amit Varma]: that was fascinating.

01:50:02.880 --> 01:50:03.880
[Amit Varma]: Tell me a bit more about that.

01:50:03.880 --> 01:50:05.480
[Amit Varma]: I mean, there's you have a whole chapter on that.

01:50:05.480 --> 01:50:10.280
[Guest]: That's, you know, it's interesting, because you always think the British sort of had the

01:50:10.280 --> 01:50:12.080
[Guest]: documents are all boring and stayed etc.

01:50:12.080 --> 01:50:15.680
[Guest]: But if you read these fortnightly reports that the British residents sent to Viceroy,

01:50:15.680 --> 01:50:19.560
[Guest]: not just from Travancore, but from any court, it is essentially a gossip sheet.

01:50:19.560 --> 01:50:20.560
[Guest]: Are these available online?

01:50:20.560 --> 01:50:21.560
[Guest]: No, they're not.

01:50:21.560 --> 01:50:24.800
[Guest]: They're in the archives, some in Delhi, but a lot in the British archives, because the

01:50:24.800 --> 01:50:28.200
[Guest]: Indian copies were largely destroyed at the time of independence, so that Nehru could

01:50:28.200 --> 01:50:30.000
[Guest]: not blackmail the princes.

01:50:30.000 --> 01:50:34.320
[Guest]: So the ones however, whatever they took, they took and put it in London, away from the reach

01:50:34.320 --> 01:50:35.920
[Guest]: of the Indian government.

01:50:35.920 --> 01:50:39.880
[Guest]: So these are gossip sheets, because knowledge is power, intelligence is power, you know

01:50:39.880 --> 01:50:44.040
[Guest]: what the weaknesses of a Raja are, who he's sleeping with, you know, whether he's homosexual,

01:50:44.040 --> 01:50:45.040
[Guest]: things like that.

01:50:45.040 --> 01:50:48.600
[Guest]: You discover little secrets like that about a man or about a ruling family.

01:50:48.600 --> 01:50:53.560
[Guest]: It's far easier to control them, you know exactly where to hit them, where it hurts.

01:50:53.560 --> 01:50:57.820
[Guest]: So what's fascinating is in this black magic episode, the British resident had his spies

01:50:57.820 --> 01:51:01.880
[Guest]: informing him exactly about how many rats were being sacrificed, where the priests came

01:51:01.880 --> 01:51:04.120
[Guest]: from, how much money they had been promised.

01:51:04.120 --> 01:51:07.680
[Guest]: Nothing escaped his eye, like he knew exactly what was happening in the palace.

01:51:07.680 --> 01:51:12.120
[Guest]: And this sets in, you know, starts turning other wheels, where the British start saying,

01:51:12.120 --> 01:51:15.280
[Guest]: oh my God, you can't have the Maharaja exposed to a condition like this, we must separate

01:51:15.280 --> 01:51:16.720
[Amit Varma]: him from his mother.

01:51:16.720 --> 01:51:21.200
[Amit Varma]: And what the junior Rani was doing to sum up, or was alleged to be doing to sum up was

01:51:21.200 --> 01:51:26.040
[Amit Varma]: carrying out rituals, which would even involve human sacrifice, where the idea was that the

01:51:26.040 --> 01:51:32.400
[Amit Varma]: senior Rani dies, and her own kid, the next Maharaja is mentally incapacitated.

01:51:32.400 --> 01:51:34.360
[Amit Varma]: So she basically becomes a queen.

01:51:34.360 --> 01:51:38.240
[Guest]: Yeah, I mean, the record seems to suggest her mother, which is Ravi Varma's younger

01:51:38.240 --> 01:51:39.240
[Guest]: daughter.

01:51:39.240 --> 01:51:42.480
[Guest]: She's the one who was the force behind this junior Rani by herself, I don't think was

01:51:42.480 --> 01:51:43.960
[Guest]: much of a believer in black magic.

01:51:43.960 --> 01:51:47.840
[Guest]: But the British often refer to the fact that the junior Rani's relations are a thoroughly

01:51:47.840 --> 01:51:48.840
[Guest]: bad lot.

01:51:48.840 --> 01:51:52.840
[Guest]: It's her brothers and her mother, they say that whenever they come to the palace, it's

01:51:52.840 --> 01:51:57.320
[Guest]: chaos, because they start putting all these plots, they start working all these plots,

01:51:57.320 --> 01:51:59.840
[Guest]: which is why finally, after this black magic and all that, the mother and the brothers

01:51:59.840 --> 01:52:00.840
[Guest]: asked to leave.

01:52:00.840 --> 01:52:04.000
[Guest]: They're told to go back to Mavelikara, which is where they come from, and not come back

01:52:04.000 --> 01:52:05.000
[Guest]: to the palace.

01:52:05.000 --> 01:52:08.040
[Guest]: They're not allowed to see the Maharaja without permission from the British, really.

01:52:08.040 --> 01:52:11.160
[Guest]: And it's only after the boy grows up and becomes king that they're finally allowed to come

01:52:11.160 --> 01:52:12.160
[Guest]: back.

01:52:12.160 --> 01:52:15.720
[Guest]: So junior Rani spends a lot of her time traveling, she stays outside the state in Ooty and Calcutta

01:52:15.720 --> 01:52:16.880
[Guest]: and places like that.

01:52:16.880 --> 01:52:18.640
[Guest]: And she's enthusiastic about going out.

01:52:18.640 --> 01:52:22.880
[Guest]: Now here there is a little bit of Sethu Lakshmi Bai's fault in the sense that the world is

01:52:22.880 --> 01:52:23.880
[Guest]: changing.

01:52:23.880 --> 01:52:27.040
[Guest]: Sethu Lakshmi Bai is still holding to that old royal protocol, because she thinks that

01:52:27.040 --> 01:52:31.680
[Guest]: is her duty to preserve the existing system, build and change through consensus and compromise,

01:52:31.680 --> 01:52:32.920
[Guest]: nothing too radical.

01:52:32.920 --> 01:52:37.840
[Guest]: And that notion of royalty as being semi-divine must be above all criticism, you know, you

01:52:37.840 --> 01:52:39.720
[Guest]: should always be seen to be perfect.

01:52:39.720 --> 01:52:42.600
[Guest]: So if you're going out for parties, if you're going out and meeting people in Calcutta,

01:52:42.600 --> 01:52:46.120
[Guest]: etc., if you're traveling, and that's costing the state a lot of money, these are things

01:52:46.120 --> 01:52:47.120
[Guest]: that can be avoided.

01:52:47.120 --> 01:52:49.160
[Guest]: In Sethu Lakshmi Bai's view, you should not do any of that.

01:52:49.160 --> 01:52:50.240
[Guest]: Why do you need to do that?

01:52:50.240 --> 01:52:51.400
[Guest]: Stay in the palace and live your life.

01:52:51.400 --> 01:52:53.080
[Guest]: Why do you want to travel and all that?

01:52:53.080 --> 01:52:56.080
[Guest]: Junior Rani is like anxious to even cross the seas and go abroad.

01:52:56.080 --> 01:52:59.440
[Guest]: So there's even in terms of their personalities, the two women don't match.

01:52:59.440 --> 01:53:01.600
[Guest]: One in the junior Rani sees the changing world.

01:53:01.600 --> 01:53:06.560
[Guest]: She wants to be part of this changing universe, this pan-Indian network of glamorous Rajas,

01:53:06.560 --> 01:53:07.600
[Guest]: Ranis and people like that.

01:53:07.600 --> 01:53:09.400
[Guest]: She wants to be part of that.

01:53:09.400 --> 01:53:11.520
[Guest]: Senior Rani does not understand it.

01:53:11.520 --> 01:53:15.440
[Guest]: Finally in 1931, November 1931, the regency comes to an end.

01:53:15.440 --> 01:53:19.440
[Guest]: The junior Rani's son comes to the throne, which essentially means that man doesn't have

01:53:19.440 --> 01:53:20.640
[Guest]: much of a personality.

01:53:20.640 --> 01:53:24.800
[Guest]: All the records suggest that he's a very gentle, wonderful human being, but as a king, somewhat

01:53:24.800 --> 01:53:30.320
[Guest]: devoid of power that he needed to wield, because all that was controlled by his mother and

01:53:30.320 --> 01:53:32.360
[Guest]: by his minister, the famous Sir C.P.

01:53:32.360 --> 01:53:36.480
[Guest]: Ramaswamy Iyer, who would be the last powerful Diwan of Travancore.

01:53:36.480 --> 01:53:41.800
[Guest]: And from this time, you start seeing Sethu Lakshmi Bai starts receiving a lot of harassment.

01:53:41.800 --> 01:53:45.240
[Guest]: And it's all kinds of petty things, you know, like it's almost payback for the seven years

01:53:45.240 --> 01:53:46.240
[Guest]: that she was in power.

01:53:46.240 --> 01:53:49.560
[Guest]: And now her sister is basically giving her payback for it.

01:53:49.560 --> 01:53:55.000
[Amit Varma]: But it struck me that she's also sort of tied into a lot of these superficial symbolic things.

01:53:55.000 --> 01:54:00.000
[Amit Varma]: For example, you know, she wants a 21 gun salute to continue after she's whatever and

01:54:00.000 --> 01:54:01.280
[Amit Varma]: all of these little petty things.

01:54:01.280 --> 01:54:05.800
[Amit Varma]: So I can understand that, okay, she's going to negotiate over whatever her royal salary

01:54:05.800 --> 01:54:08.600
[Amit Varma]: is and royal pension is or whatever.

01:54:08.600 --> 01:54:12.720
[Guest]: But there are also these other petty things, which, for example, she's told that she must

01:54:12.720 --> 01:54:14.800
[Guest]: come and call on the Maharaja every two weeks.

01:54:14.800 --> 01:54:15.800
[Guest]: And she's like, I'm older than him.

01:54:15.800 --> 01:54:16.800
[Guest]: I'm his aunt.

01:54:16.800 --> 01:54:17.800
[Guest]: Why should I go and call on him?

01:54:17.800 --> 01:54:19.440
[Guest]: The tradition is that he should come and call on me.

01:54:19.440 --> 01:54:20.440
[Guest]: So then that proposal is gone.

01:54:20.440 --> 01:54:22.280
[Guest]: Then they say, oh, your daughters must come and see him.

01:54:22.280 --> 01:54:23.280
[Guest]: She says, fine.

01:54:23.280 --> 01:54:25.800
[Guest]: But when the daughters are sent, they're told to meet the Maharaja alone.

01:54:25.800 --> 01:54:28.120
[Guest]: And she says, no, my daughters are girls, they're children.

01:54:28.120 --> 01:54:31.000
[Guest]: The Maharaja, that is the junior Rani's son, is a practical stranger to them.

01:54:31.000 --> 01:54:32.200
[Guest]: They don't know him very well.

01:54:32.200 --> 01:54:34.480
[Guest]: Till they grow up, once they grow up, they can see him alone.

01:54:34.480 --> 01:54:38.200
[Guest]: But till they grow up, I will not allow my daughters to see the Maharaja by themselves.

01:54:38.200 --> 01:54:39.200
[Guest]: Their father must be present.

01:54:39.200 --> 01:54:41.400
[Guest]: Now, the junior Rani hates the senior's husband.

01:54:41.400 --> 01:54:42.960
[Guest]: So why would she want him in the room?

01:54:42.960 --> 01:54:46.840
[Guest]: So they say, no, as head of the family, he may not be able to persuade you to come and

01:54:46.840 --> 01:54:49.280
[Guest]: see him, but he definitely has control over the children.

01:54:49.280 --> 01:54:50.640
[Guest]: He's their official guardian.

01:54:50.640 --> 01:54:51.640
[Guest]: So he can come on.

01:54:51.640 --> 01:54:52.640
[Guest]: She has no option.

01:54:52.640 --> 01:54:53.640
[Guest]: She has to live with that.

01:54:53.640 --> 01:54:56.840
[Guest]: Then they say, all your jewelry must be sent to us for inspection every six months.

01:54:56.840 --> 01:54:58.840
[Guest]: And Sethulakshmi Bai sees through the insult.

01:54:58.840 --> 01:55:00.640
[Guest]: She's like, this is a way to get my jewelry back.

01:55:00.640 --> 01:55:02.480
[Guest]: It has nothing to do with inspection.

01:55:02.480 --> 01:55:03.480
[Guest]: It's harassment.

01:55:03.480 --> 01:55:06.360
[Guest]: Like every six months, if you keep sending your personal jewelry for inspection, she's

01:55:06.360 --> 01:55:07.360
[Guest]: like, just take the jewelry.

01:55:07.360 --> 01:55:10.720
[Guest]: I'll make my private jewelry with my private money, with my income, my pension, and so

01:55:10.720 --> 01:55:11.720
[Guest]: on.

01:55:11.720 --> 01:55:15.200
[Guest]: So at one point she wants to travel, they won't let her travel.

01:55:15.200 --> 01:55:20.220
[Guest]: There's even petty things, for example, as Maharani of the state, she's entitled to guards

01:55:20.220 --> 01:55:22.440
[Guest]: and certain protection.

01:55:22.440 --> 01:55:26.680
[Guest]: Now, she does not like living in Trivandrum once her sister's son comes to power because

01:55:26.680 --> 01:55:27.680
[Guest]: it's unhealthy.

01:55:27.680 --> 01:55:29.280
[Guest]: She doesn't want to stay there.

01:55:29.280 --> 01:55:32.600
[Guest]: She builds a private house for herself outside Trivandrum in a village and she wants to retire

01:55:32.600 --> 01:55:33.600
[Guest]: and live in the village.

01:55:33.600 --> 01:55:38.080
[Guest]: But they say, oh, but your protection must come with you because you're the queen.

01:55:38.080 --> 01:55:41.640
[Guest]: So instead of guards being posted there for a certain number of days, every day the guards

01:55:41.640 --> 01:55:44.640
[Guest]: have to be changed, which means every day the guards have to go to the village, come

01:55:44.640 --> 01:55:45.640
[Guest]: back to Trivandrum.

01:55:45.640 --> 01:55:46.640
[Guest]: And who's got to pay for this?

01:55:46.640 --> 01:55:48.520
[Guest]: The senior Rani has to supply the money for this.

01:55:48.520 --> 01:55:51.200
[Guest]: So she's like, you're trying to bleed me, then don't give me guards because I can't

01:55:51.200 --> 01:55:55.240
[Guest]: afford to have guards moving up and down when they can stay there for 15 days at a stretch.

01:55:55.240 --> 01:55:56.240
[Guest]: You know, let them stay there.

01:55:56.240 --> 01:55:58.000
[Guest]: Why do you want to keep moving them up and down?

01:55:58.000 --> 01:55:59.000
[Guest]: There's that.

01:55:59.000 --> 01:56:00.720
[Guest]: At one point, they take over her ancestral estates.

01:56:00.720 --> 01:56:03.440
[Guest]: A senior Rani, she controls a 15,000 acre estate.

01:56:03.440 --> 01:56:06.280
[Guest]: And it is through that that her servants are paid, her establishment is paid.

01:56:06.280 --> 01:56:07.820
[Guest]: She doesn't have a separate income.

01:56:07.820 --> 01:56:11.000
[Guest]: That is what supplies her, her chief source of personal income.

01:56:11.000 --> 01:56:12.000
[Guest]: They take over that.

01:56:12.000 --> 01:56:15.280
[Guest]: And the British basically shut their eyes and allow the Maharaja to do it.

01:56:15.280 --> 01:56:17.280
[Guest]: Because the British are coming from a patriarchal thing.

01:56:17.280 --> 01:56:20.000
[Guest]: They're like, yeah, Maharani must listen to the Maharaja.

01:56:20.000 --> 01:56:21.620
[Guest]: She can't independently work.

01:56:21.620 --> 01:56:24.800
[Guest]: They don't understand that in the matrilineal system, family matters are decided by the

01:56:24.800 --> 01:56:25.960
[Guest]: head of the family.

01:56:25.960 --> 01:56:26.960
[Guest]: That is not gendered.

01:56:26.960 --> 01:56:29.880
[Guest]: The head of the family is the oldest member of the family, which whether it's male or

01:56:29.880 --> 01:56:31.440
[Guest]: female, you have to listen to that person.

01:56:31.440 --> 01:56:36.200
[Guest]: Technically, Sethulakshmi is the head of the family, but she has no voice there.

01:56:36.200 --> 01:56:41.040
[Guest]: She, you know, when she rules, when she finishes her reign in 1931, she's ruled exceedingly

01:56:41.040 --> 01:56:42.040
[Guest]: well.

01:56:42.040 --> 01:56:44.400
[Guest]: The British love her, nationalists like Gandhiji love her.

01:56:44.400 --> 01:56:45.400
[Guest]: The people respect her.

01:56:45.400 --> 01:56:48.640
[Guest]: And you find this even in records to the late 1940s.

01:56:48.640 --> 01:56:52.000
[Guest]: She's been out of power for 18 years, not seen by anybody before 18 years.

01:56:52.000 --> 01:56:55.640
[Guest]: But even VP Menon and his people who come to negotiate the integration with the Indian

01:56:55.640 --> 01:57:00.680
[Guest]: Union say that Sethulakshmi is far more popular than the junior Rani and her son, who've been

01:57:00.680 --> 01:57:02.440
[Guest]: ruling for the last 17 years.

01:57:02.440 --> 01:57:06.600
[Guest]: Because her memory is still extremely fond as far as the people are concerned.

01:57:06.600 --> 01:57:10.720
[Guest]: So she has to really negotiate with the Maharaja and finally get the British involved to get

01:57:10.720 --> 01:57:13.040
[Guest]: a decent pension, which is 75,000 rupees a year.

01:57:13.040 --> 01:57:16.280
[Guest]: Now, you look at what North Indian Rajas of much smaller, poorer states were spending

01:57:16.280 --> 01:57:19.040
[Guest]: 75,000 was a very modest amount.

01:57:19.040 --> 01:57:23.240
[Guest]: So Maharaja with great resistance finally satisfies and gives her a 75,000 rupee pension.

01:57:23.240 --> 01:57:26.320
[Guest]: She wanted more, but she gets 75,000 rupees.

01:57:26.320 --> 01:57:32.420
[Guest]: His 18 year old brother or 19 year old brother casually gives him a one lakh rupee allowance.

01:57:32.420 --> 01:57:33.420
[Guest]: This is all a signal.

01:57:33.420 --> 01:57:38.000
[Guest]: So you rule for seven years, work hard and actually rule the state, you get only 75,000.

01:57:38.000 --> 01:57:42.000
[Guest]: My younger brother, who's just turned 19, a teenager, he gets one lakh a year.

01:57:42.000 --> 01:57:43.000
[Guest]: That's his allowance.

01:57:43.000 --> 01:57:47.200
[Guest]: So all of this makes her realize that she is essentially becoming a second class citizen.

01:57:47.200 --> 01:57:52.200
[Guest]: This kind of pettiness you see even now in government, right, it's the kind of things

01:57:52.200 --> 01:57:56.000
[Guest]: the current ruling dispensation, for example, does against a certain family, for example,

01:57:56.000 --> 01:58:01.520
[Guest]: or petty things like denying leader of opposition post on certain technicalities, reducing somebody's

01:58:01.520 --> 01:58:02.520
[Guest]: security, etc.

01:58:02.520 --> 01:58:06.160
[Guest]: Which is not a bad thing, frankly, you still have security, but it's all about making them

01:58:06.160 --> 01:58:09.400
[Guest]: feel like you are no longer what you used to be.

01:58:09.400 --> 01:58:10.640
[Guest]: And that happened a lot here as well.

01:58:10.640 --> 01:58:13.560
[Guest]: She was increasingly marginalized and cornered.

01:58:13.560 --> 01:58:17.480
[Guest]: And finally, in the 1940s, she had an estate that she purchased privately in the hills.

01:58:17.480 --> 01:58:20.600
[Guest]: So she couldn't, her family could have summer vacations there, taken over by the state.

01:58:20.600 --> 01:58:23.080
[Guest]: It had to wait till after independence that she got it back.

01:58:23.080 --> 01:58:25.320
[Guest]: The government of India gave it back to her, not the government of Trivandrum.

01:58:25.320 --> 01:58:28.880
[Guest]: For 10 years, it was in the hands of the Maharaja because he said, no, I'm going to take over

01:58:28.880 --> 01:58:29.880
[Guest]: it.

01:58:29.880 --> 01:58:33.080
[Guest]: So her private residences, she was told by the 1940s, you can't stay in your private

01:58:33.080 --> 01:58:35.280
[Guest]: houses, you must live in Trivandrum.

01:58:35.280 --> 01:58:38.680
[Guest]: And because her estate has been taken over, it means her servants are controlled by the

01:58:38.680 --> 01:58:42.240
[Guest]: junior Rani's son, her house is controlled by the junior Rani's son.

01:58:42.240 --> 01:58:46.040
[Guest]: And perhaps the greatest tragedy of her life, that palace was built by her, she raised her

01:58:46.040 --> 01:58:47.040
[Guest]: children there.

01:58:47.040 --> 01:58:50.840
[Guest]: When the partition of family properties took place in the 1970s, the Maharaja claimed that

01:58:50.840 --> 01:58:54.360
[Guest]: palace and even though she went to the Supreme Court, she didn't get it.

01:58:54.360 --> 01:58:58.320
[Guest]: So the palace she built, in which she lived, in which she ruled, in which her children

01:58:58.320 --> 01:59:01.360
[Guest]: were raised, that also went to her sister's son.

01:59:01.360 --> 01:59:05.600
[Guest]: So, you know, it was no wonder that as soon as independence came, the Maharani had two

01:59:05.600 --> 01:59:06.600
[Guest]: daughters.

01:59:06.600 --> 01:59:07.920
[Guest]: The older daughter said, I am done with being royalty.

01:59:07.920 --> 01:59:10.520
[Guest]: I mean, this is an oppressive, harassed sort of existence.

01:59:10.520 --> 01:59:12.560
[Guest]: We've got, it's like living in a gilded cage.

01:59:12.560 --> 01:59:15.920
[Guest]: You've got all the servants and technically the money and the privileges, but you have

01:59:15.920 --> 01:59:16.920
[Guest]: no freedom.

01:59:16.920 --> 01:59:19.960
[Guest]: You can't go from one room to the other without being followed by servants who are all paid

01:59:19.960 --> 01:59:21.880
[Guest]: by the other center.

01:59:21.880 --> 01:59:23.720
[Guest]: The other ones were actually in power.

01:59:23.720 --> 01:59:24.920
[Guest]: So this resentment builds up.

01:59:24.920 --> 01:59:26.880
[Guest]: So the daughter says, I'm done being royalty.

01:59:26.880 --> 01:59:28.560
[Guest]: I'm going to Bangalore.

01:59:28.560 --> 01:59:32.560
[Guest]: She goes off to Bangalore, buys a private house there, puts all her children into school.

01:59:32.560 --> 01:59:37.000
[Guest]: So her, from being Her Highness Uttaram Tirunel Lalitha Amba Bai Tamburan, second princess

01:59:37.000 --> 01:59:39.800
[Guest]: of Travancore, the girl becomes simply Lalitha Varma.

01:59:39.800 --> 01:59:40.800
[Guest]: She gives up her title.

01:59:40.800 --> 01:59:44.840
[Guest]: She becomes just Lalitha Varma, puts all her children into public schools, starts driving

01:59:44.840 --> 01:59:46.080
[Guest]: her own car.

01:59:46.080 --> 01:59:48.160
[Guest]: And it's an education for her from day one.

01:59:48.160 --> 01:59:52.520
[Guest]: There's this wonderful story in the family about how she went to Bangalore club to shop.

01:59:52.520 --> 01:59:53.960
[Guest]: Bangalore club has these shops.

01:59:53.960 --> 01:59:55.760
[Guest]: And this is 1949, soon after she's arrived.

01:59:55.760 --> 01:59:59.120
[Guest]: So she's put all the things in the basket and she's taken to the till.

01:59:59.120 --> 02:00:01.560
[Guest]: And the lady says, that'll be 89 rupees, madam.

02:00:01.560 --> 02:00:05.340
[Guest]: And she says, what are rupees because she's never actually dealt with currency.

02:00:05.340 --> 02:00:06.520
[Guest]: She understands the vague concept.

02:00:06.520 --> 02:00:10.120
[Guest]: So her driver from behind is to say, don't worry, let her go, I'll pay because she's

02:00:10.120 --> 02:00:13.720
[Guest]: as you know, alien to this independent life as that.

02:00:13.720 --> 02:00:18.200
[Guest]: But from there, she starts becoming a very autonomous figure, becomes, as her children

02:00:18.200 --> 02:00:21.320
[Guest]: say, her greatest ambition in life was to be a housewife, because she had seen what

02:00:21.320 --> 02:00:22.320
[Guest]: power did.

02:00:22.320 --> 02:00:26.440
[Guest]: She had seen what palaces and that kind of that quest for money and power could do.

02:00:26.440 --> 02:00:27.440
[Guest]: She didn't want any of that.

02:00:27.440 --> 02:00:31.000
[Guest]: She just wanted her children to be happy, almost middle class people who had little

02:00:31.000 --> 02:00:33.520
[Guest]: jobs and little things and they all live together happily.

02:00:33.520 --> 02:00:35.280
[Guest]: And that is the life she wanted.

02:00:35.280 --> 02:00:40.500
[Guest]: The Maharani Sethulakshmi Bai would come and the story, she came first in 1951.

02:00:40.500 --> 02:00:44.480
[Guest]: And she was scandalized to discover that her children were crossing the road to go to school.

02:00:44.480 --> 02:00:47.320
[Guest]: Because the school was the Baldwin Girls School on Richmond Road in Bangalore, just across

02:00:47.320 --> 02:00:48.320
[Guest]: their gate.

02:00:48.320 --> 02:00:49.320
[Guest]: And their gate was here.

02:00:49.320 --> 02:00:52.400
[Guest]: She said, no, no, no, how these poor children look at them with their heavy bags, and they're

02:00:52.400 --> 02:00:55.080
[Guest]: going to school walking and they have to cross the road, it's very dangerous.

02:00:55.080 --> 02:00:57.920
[Guest]: So while she was there, she insisted children go by car.

02:00:57.920 --> 02:01:00.160
[Guest]: And she had this stretch limo, a Humber.

02:01:00.160 --> 02:01:03.520
[Guest]: All these granddaughters of hers would be put into this car and taken to school on the

02:01:03.520 --> 02:01:04.520
[Guest]: other side.

02:01:04.520 --> 02:01:07.440
[Guest]: And the story goes that in those days, Richmond Road was so narrow that when the front of

02:01:07.440 --> 02:01:11.040
[Guest]: the car was in the school, the back was still in the house.

02:01:11.040 --> 02:01:13.960
[Guest]: That is the kind of world they had to start adjusting to.

02:01:13.960 --> 02:01:20.440
[Guest]: Then of course, 1950s, ironically for a family that had all this protocol, 300 servants around

02:01:20.440 --> 02:01:24.160
[Guest]: them, you know, Martha and Audma created all this artificial vocabulary, they're always

02:01:24.160 --> 02:01:26.080
[Guest]: referred to as Highnesses and all of that.

02:01:26.080 --> 02:01:27.080
[Guest]: What happens in Kerala?

02:01:27.080 --> 02:01:28.080
[Guest]: The commies come to power.

02:01:28.080 --> 02:01:32.160
[Guest]: One day, Sethu Lakshmi wakes up and discovers her servants in the palace.

02:01:32.160 --> 02:01:35.600
[Guest]: She's sent away most of them because the privy purse the Maharaja gets, he doesn't support

02:01:35.600 --> 02:01:36.600
[Guest]: her from that.

02:01:36.600 --> 02:01:41.160
[Guest]: She has to live out of her own minor income of 50,000 rupees a year that the government

02:01:41.160 --> 02:01:42.400
[Guest]: of India has bestowed on her.

02:01:42.400 --> 02:01:44.000
[Guest]: She has to manage her palace with that.

02:01:44.000 --> 02:01:49.240
[Guest]: So she's reduced her staff to 50 servants and 25 work for 10 days and then 15 days and

02:01:49.240 --> 02:01:50.440
[Guest]: then the other 25 take over.

02:01:50.440 --> 02:01:54.960
[Guest]: So very small establishment, but they formed a union and someone's gone and put the communist

02:01:54.960 --> 02:01:56.800
[Guest]: flag on top of the palace.

02:01:56.800 --> 02:01:58.880
[Guest]: And that's when she discovers, why am I even living here?

02:01:58.880 --> 02:02:00.160
[Guest]: You know, I'm not welcome here.

02:02:00.160 --> 02:02:03.320
[Guest]: The Maharaja doesn't want me, doesn't seem to respect me.

02:02:03.320 --> 02:02:05.880
[Guest]: I have to maintain a palace at great personal expense.

02:02:05.880 --> 02:02:06.880
[Guest]: My daughters have left.

02:02:06.880 --> 02:02:09.640
[Guest]: The younger daughter had gone off to Madras by then, where her husband became a lawyer

02:02:09.640 --> 02:02:11.720
[Guest]: because he wanted to have a profession.

02:02:11.720 --> 02:02:15.680
[Guest]: She decides to move to Bangalore and this woman, you know, in the middle of a siege

02:02:15.680 --> 02:02:19.360
[Guest]: practically by her servants, where the police are deployed to make sure that she can safely

02:02:19.360 --> 02:02:21.760
[Guest]: get out of the palace because they're refusing to operate the palace.

02:02:21.760 --> 02:02:23.480
[Guest]: Palaces are not built like individual houses.

02:02:23.480 --> 02:02:27.200
[Guest]: You can't just go and cook your food in the kitchen and not that she knew how to cook.

02:02:27.200 --> 02:02:30.040
[Guest]: So you know, you needed your servants to operate it.

02:02:30.040 --> 02:02:32.120
[Guest]: She leaves the palace and never comes back.

02:02:32.120 --> 02:02:34.960
[Guest]: So she gets out of the palace, sits in her car.

02:02:34.960 --> 02:02:37.580
[Guest]: First she drives to the Padmanabhaswamy temple, the family deity.

02:02:37.580 --> 02:02:39.440
[Guest]: In the car, she turns around saying, forgive me.

02:02:39.440 --> 02:02:40.440
[Guest]: I'm not staying anymore.

02:02:40.440 --> 02:02:41.440
[Guest]: You are now in my heart.

02:02:41.440 --> 02:02:45.120
[Guest]: I will never be able to see you again, goes to the railway station, which is the last

02:02:45.120 --> 02:02:48.440
[Guest]: time in her life where a crowd of people bow to her because they recognize the Maharani

02:02:48.440 --> 02:02:49.440
[Guest]: of Travancore.

02:02:49.440 --> 02:02:50.440
[Guest]: They know who she is.

02:02:50.440 --> 02:02:52.000
[Guest]: She gets in a train, first goes to Madras.

02:02:52.000 --> 02:02:56.280
[Guest]: From there, stays with her younger daughter for a while, then drives off to Bangalore.

02:02:56.280 --> 02:03:00.360
[Guest]: And in Bangalore, she purchases the house next to her sister's, constructs a little

02:03:00.360 --> 02:03:02.440
[Guest]: bungalow there and it's called Srinivas.

02:03:02.440 --> 02:03:07.160
[Guest]: And there's this wonderful envelope, you know, her title fully was Her Highness Shri Padmanabha

02:03:07.160 --> 02:03:11.560
[Guest]: Sevini Vanchi Dharma Varthini Raja Rajeshwari, Maharani Pooradam Dhirnaal Sethu Lakshmibai

02:03:11.560 --> 02:03:15.080
[Guest]: Maharaja, Artingal Moortha Thamburan, Companion of the Most Imperial Order of the Crown of

02:03:15.080 --> 02:03:16.080
[Guest]: India.

02:03:16.080 --> 02:03:17.240
[Guest]: That was her full title.

02:03:17.240 --> 02:03:21.000
[Guest]: But as soon as she moves to Bangalore, she starts signing her letters, etc. simply Srimati

02:03:21.000 --> 02:03:22.280
[Guest]: Sethu Lakshmibai.

02:03:22.280 --> 02:03:23.280
[Guest]: She's given up her title.

02:03:23.280 --> 02:03:26.520
[Guest]: Like her daughter, she just decides to become a nobody.

02:03:26.520 --> 02:03:30.680
[Guest]: And then after this, from 1957, she dies in 1985.

02:03:30.680 --> 02:03:34.760
[Guest]: All these two and a half decades that she lived, she never went back to Kerala.

02:03:34.760 --> 02:03:37.720
[Guest]: And slowly the state starts acquiring her various properties.

02:03:37.720 --> 02:03:40.920
[Guest]: She's told one fine day that the house that she'd built in the village where she wasn't

02:03:40.920 --> 02:03:44.360
[Guest]: allowed to stay by the Maharaja, it was still hers, state wants to start an agriculture

02:03:44.360 --> 02:03:45.360
[Guest]: college there.

02:03:45.360 --> 02:03:46.360
[Guest]: She says, fine, take it.

02:03:46.360 --> 02:03:50.080
[Guest]: Her husband had a house by the beach where he kept his things, etc.

02:03:50.080 --> 02:03:53.000
[Guest]: State got involved and said, we are acquiring this for tourism purposes.

02:03:53.000 --> 02:03:54.000
[Guest]: No option.

02:03:54.000 --> 02:03:55.600
[Guest]: You have to give it up to the state.

02:03:55.600 --> 02:04:01.320
[Guest]: Slowly everything has gone till finally in the 1970s, they want to set up a medical research

02:04:01.320 --> 02:04:03.760
[Guest]: facility in her official palace.

02:04:03.760 --> 02:04:07.520
[Guest]: Although the Maharaja is the owner and he eventually gets the compensation for it.

02:04:07.520 --> 02:04:11.280
[Guest]: They can't do it without her permission because she's in possession of the keys.

02:04:11.280 --> 02:04:15.640
[Guest]: So the man comes, MS Valyatan, the celebrated medical grandee.

02:04:15.640 --> 02:04:20.000
[Guest]: So he shows up and he told me this, that he showed up there and many people told her don't

02:04:20.000 --> 02:04:21.000
[Guest]: do this.

02:04:21.000 --> 02:04:24.120
[Guest]: How are you giving up your last thing left in Kerala to somebody?

02:04:24.120 --> 02:04:26.640
[Guest]: And she sort of, he misses his flight.

02:04:26.640 --> 02:04:30.640
[Guest]: By the time he gets to her house in Bangalore, it's midnight, this is in 76 or so.

02:04:30.640 --> 02:04:31.640
[Guest]: And she's waiting.

02:04:31.640 --> 02:04:32.640
[Guest]: She's awake.

02:04:32.640 --> 02:04:33.640
[Guest]: And her daughter says, of course, she's awake.

02:04:33.640 --> 02:04:34.640
[Guest]: She's awake.

02:04:34.640 --> 02:04:35.640
[Guest]: She's waiting to sign the papers.

02:04:35.640 --> 02:04:36.640
[Guest]: And he brings her the paper.

02:04:36.640 --> 02:04:40.720
[Guest]: She signs her right over the palace of claims that gives up her possession, hands over the

02:04:40.720 --> 02:04:41.720
[Guest]: keys.

02:04:41.720 --> 02:04:45.520
[Guest]: And then she looks up to him, holds up her hands and says, Valyatan, this is my freedom

02:04:45.520 --> 02:04:46.520
[Guest]: at midnight.

02:04:46.520 --> 02:04:47.520
[Guest]: Because now she has nothing.

02:04:47.520 --> 02:04:52.680
[Guest]: Like for a woman who was queen from the age of five, from the age of five, she had a 21

02:04:52.680 --> 02:04:53.680
[Guest]: gun salute.

02:04:53.680 --> 02:04:54.680
[Guest]: She had 300 servants.

02:04:54.680 --> 02:04:55.680
[Guest]: Her own father would bow to her.

02:04:55.680 --> 02:04:57.040
[Guest]: Her husband refers to her highness.

02:04:57.040 --> 02:04:58.760
[Guest]: She's never known a life different.

02:04:58.760 --> 02:05:00.880
[Guest]: She's never known another existence.

02:05:00.880 --> 02:05:04.800
[Guest]: From there, suddenly, and she turns to a family member and says, once I had a kingdom, but

02:05:04.800 --> 02:05:05.920
[Guest]: that is gone.

02:05:05.920 --> 02:05:08.720
[Guest]: Then I thought I had my palaces, but that those are gone, too.

02:05:08.720 --> 02:05:09.880
[Guest]: Then I thought I had this house.

02:05:09.880 --> 02:05:13.680
[Guest]: But now I can only say I have this room because that is what her life is reduced to that one

02:05:13.680 --> 02:05:15.680
[Guest]: room where she's increasingly crippled.

02:05:15.680 --> 02:05:16.680
[Guest]: She can't go out.

02:05:16.680 --> 02:05:17.680
[Unknown]: And she's stuck there.

02:05:17.680 --> 02:05:22.060
[Guest]: And, you know, all as a grandson told me, all she sees is the sun and the morning and

02:05:22.060 --> 02:05:23.720
[Guest]: evening happening through her windows.

02:05:23.720 --> 02:05:26.880
[Guest]: And she's just sitting there in that room for the next 20 years of her life.

02:05:26.880 --> 02:05:31.880
[Guest]: And when finally she dies in 1985, she's cremated in an electric crematorium, surrounded just

02:05:31.880 --> 02:05:34.680
[Guest]: by family members like anybody's grandmother.

02:05:34.680 --> 02:05:38.440
[Guest]: Nobody would know this was a person who once dealt with Gandhi, who once dealt with Mussolini's

02:05:38.440 --> 02:05:41.900
[Guest]: daughter, who once impressed Rabindranath Tagore, who once ruled and controlled the

02:05:41.900 --> 02:05:43.880
[Guest]: destinies of five million people.

02:05:43.880 --> 02:05:44.880
[Guest]: None of that.

02:05:44.880 --> 02:05:46.640
[Guest]: She disappeared as a complete nobody.

02:05:46.640 --> 02:05:51.680
[Guest]: And for me, that arc was fascinating to think that even now for people to give up power,

02:05:51.680 --> 02:05:52.680
[Guest]: it's so difficult.

02:05:52.680 --> 02:05:56.280
[Guest]: You know, when you have power, it's very difficult to give up your conveniences and enjoying

02:05:56.280 --> 02:05:58.960
[Guest]: that power, to give up money, to become a nobody.

02:05:58.960 --> 02:06:03.680
[Guest]: And here was this woman who, from the beginning, first she couldn't produce the melee, then,

02:06:03.680 --> 02:06:07.560
[Guest]: you know, she couldn't keep herself on good terms with her sister.

02:06:07.560 --> 02:06:11.040
[Guest]: Then she was harassed a great deal by her sister and her son, the Maharaja, made to

02:06:11.040 --> 02:06:13.440
[Guest]: feel unwelcome in the royal family itself.

02:06:13.440 --> 02:06:17.240
[Guest]: Communists sieged her palace and sort of took over control and she had to leave.

02:06:17.240 --> 02:06:19.400
[Guest]: Her palace itself was seized by various people.

02:06:19.400 --> 02:06:22.200
[Guest]: Her children didn't want any part of her royal legacy.

02:06:22.200 --> 02:06:25.800
[Guest]: And she ends up, you know, accepting the fact that she's become a nobody.

02:06:25.800 --> 02:06:31.320
[Guest]: And for a Brahmin-controlled palace, where even her meals were cooked by sacred thread-wearing

02:06:31.320 --> 02:06:35.520
[Guest]: high caste groups, by the end of her life, it was Christian maids and Nair, you know,

02:06:35.520 --> 02:06:37.640
[Guest]: so-called Shudra women who are cooking her meals.

02:06:37.640 --> 02:06:38.640
[Guest]: And she accepted that.

02:06:38.640 --> 02:06:40.080
[Guest]: And she lived with that sort of thing.

02:06:40.080 --> 02:06:45.080
[Guest]: And that acceptance of her fate, understanding that the page of history had turned, not only

02:06:45.080 --> 02:06:48.860
[Guest]: was the royal class irrelevant, she in particular was doubly irrelevant.

02:06:48.860 --> 02:06:52.800
[Guest]: And she had been reduced to a footnote in the history of Travancore for all her achievements.

02:06:52.800 --> 02:06:54.880
[Guest]: The future was controlled by the junior maharajas.

02:06:54.880 --> 02:06:58.840
[Guest]: Ironically, the junior Maharani's family still live in a palace in Trivandrum.

02:06:58.840 --> 02:07:01.040
[Guest]: And again, I didn't include this in the book.

02:07:01.040 --> 02:07:04.600
[Guest]: But if you look at the National Archives, there is this tone of surprise because VP

02:07:04.600 --> 02:07:08.760
[Guest]: Menon and his colleague Velody, they come to Trivandrum to negotiate Privy Purse and

02:07:08.760 --> 02:07:10.520
[Guest]: the allowances, etc.

02:07:10.520 --> 02:07:14.960
[Guest]: And Velody writes a letter to VP Menon in Delhi saying that, I was completely startled

02:07:14.960 --> 02:07:18.720
[Guest]: by the fact that Maharaja is negotiating what amount he should get, what his mother, brother,

02:07:18.720 --> 02:07:20.440
[Guest]: his family members should get.

02:07:20.440 --> 02:07:22.480
[Guest]: But he did not once refer to the senior Maharani.

02:07:22.480 --> 02:07:26.520
[Guest]: It felt as though she doesn't even exist as far as the Maharaja is concerned.

02:07:26.520 --> 02:07:28.240
[Guest]: And they were surprised by the pettiness of it.

02:07:28.240 --> 02:07:31.600
[Guest]: They were surprised that he wouldn't even acknowledge her existence to begin with.

02:07:31.600 --> 02:07:35.880
[Guest]: As small things, for example, you know, again, it's not in the book, but in the archives,

02:07:35.880 --> 02:07:39.800
[Guest]: they talk about how the Maharaja gets electricity exemption, free electricity for himself and

02:07:39.800 --> 02:07:42.200
[Guest]: his brother's palace, nothing for the senior Rani.

02:07:42.200 --> 02:07:44.480
[Guest]: So she is now, she's not getting a share of the Privy Purse.

02:07:44.480 --> 02:07:47.200
[Guest]: She's getting 50,000 rupees as allowance in a year.

02:07:47.200 --> 02:07:52.320
[Guest]: She has to maintain a palace, no privileges other than, you know, the money that she gets.

02:07:52.320 --> 02:07:55.160
[Guest]: And you know, not even mentioned as a factor in the negotiations.

02:07:55.160 --> 02:07:58.760
[Guest]: Finally, it's a VP Menon and Velodi themselves go to the senior Maharani.

02:07:58.760 --> 02:08:01.760
[Guest]: They find out from her, and she's got pretty modest demand.

02:08:01.760 --> 02:08:04.480
[Guest]: She's like, my children should not be treated unfairly.

02:08:04.480 --> 02:08:08.900
[Guest]: If the other family is getting certain allowances, my children should get something similar.

02:08:08.900 --> 02:08:09.900
[Guest]: In the end, they don't.

02:08:09.900 --> 02:08:12.160
[Guest]: They get a smaller allowance because they have no power.

02:08:12.160 --> 02:08:15.120
[Guest]: And it's interesting to see that although technically a royalty, although technically

02:08:15.120 --> 02:08:18.080
[Guest]: you're a queen, you're entirely powerless.

02:08:18.080 --> 02:08:22.200
[Guest]: And having to live through that, I thought was interesting, whereas a junior Rani's family,

02:08:22.200 --> 02:08:23.200
[Guest]: they continue to live there.

02:08:23.200 --> 02:08:27.920
[Guest]: I think the last time the Maharani's met was before Sethu Lakshmibai leaves for Bangalore

02:08:27.920 --> 02:08:29.200
[Guest]: in 1957.

02:08:29.200 --> 02:08:33.280
[Guest]: And then they meet once more in their life, which is 23 years, almost 23 years later in

02:08:33.280 --> 02:08:34.280
[Guest]: 1979.

02:08:34.280 --> 02:08:37.880
[Guest]: Four years before the junior Rani dies, and you know, six years before the senior Rani

02:08:37.880 --> 02:08:42.920
[Guest]: dies, the junior Rani calls up and expresses a desire to meet her older sister.

02:08:42.920 --> 02:08:46.720
[Guest]: And the family tells me that she didn't want, the senior Rani didn't want to meet because

02:08:46.720 --> 02:08:51.200
[Guest]: here she was a bedridden in Bangalore in this house and you know, she didn't feel like,

02:08:51.200 --> 02:08:54.560
[Guest]: this was a past that she had forgotten that she, that was a different person and this

02:08:54.560 --> 02:08:55.560
[Guest]: was a different person.

02:08:55.560 --> 02:08:56.560
[Guest]: A toxic world she left behind.

02:08:56.560 --> 02:08:59.480
[Guest]: She didn't want to be part of that, but she couldn't say no either.

02:08:59.480 --> 02:09:02.720
[Guest]: So they came, they had a nice little meeting, etc.

02:09:02.720 --> 02:09:03.960
[Unknown]: And that was that.

02:09:03.960 --> 02:09:08.080
[Guest]: And you know, she did ask one thing apparently, and this I'm not putting the book because

02:09:08.080 --> 02:09:11.720
[Guest]: I can't substantiate it with documents, but interviews with her family members, they told

02:09:11.720 --> 02:09:15.800
[Guest]: me that she did ask the junior Rani, that why are you even taking my palace, you know,

02:09:15.800 --> 02:09:19.960
[Guest]: that palace which she built, where her children were brought up, which was home for them,

02:09:19.960 --> 02:09:22.760
[Guest]: their final property in Kerala, why are you even claiming that?

02:09:22.760 --> 02:09:26.200
[Guest]: And junior Rani had some answer for it saying, oh no, but you know, something on the other.

02:09:26.200 --> 02:09:28.960
[Guest]: And she said, you know, she just smiled and she said, okay, fine.

02:09:28.960 --> 02:09:32.760
[Guest]: Clearly this is, even asking for that much is too much as far as she was concerned.

02:09:32.760 --> 02:09:34.240
[Guest]: So she said, forget it.

02:09:34.240 --> 02:09:37.680
[Guest]: And her daughter's children, you know, they have very little awareness of their royal

02:09:37.680 --> 02:09:38.680
[Guest]: heritage.

02:09:38.680 --> 02:09:39.680
[Guest]: I mean, they're aware of it.

02:09:39.680 --> 02:09:40.680
[Guest]: They know that it's there.

02:09:40.680 --> 02:09:43.680
[Guest]: And they know their grandmother was somebody important, but they have very few royal heirs

02:09:43.680 --> 02:09:45.000
[Guest]: because they're like, she abandoned it.

02:09:45.000 --> 02:09:46.000
[Guest]: She'd gave it up.

02:09:46.000 --> 02:09:50.080
[Guest]: So why should we, you know, feel like we are entitled to something?

02:09:50.080 --> 02:09:52.720
[Guest]: And I thought that, well, there was a tragic element to it.

02:09:52.720 --> 02:09:56.840
[Guest]: I mean, there is criticism that she presided over a feudal court, it was casteist and she

02:09:56.840 --> 02:10:00.200
[Guest]: of course had her weaknesses and her flaws naturally.

02:10:00.200 --> 02:10:04.320
[Guest]: But on the whole, if you look at the story, you know, it ends on a very tragic note.

02:10:04.320 --> 02:10:08.120
[Guest]: And I was just keen to sort of make sure that, you know, this lady who led this very remarkable

02:10:08.120 --> 02:10:12.040
[Guest]: life, forget the personal drama, even what she achieved in that space of seven years,

02:10:12.040 --> 02:10:16.360
[Guest]: those seven years are just remarkable, the kind of reforms and changes she made, Keralites

02:10:16.360 --> 02:10:19.800
[Guest]: are still enjoying the benefits of those seven years, the same roads, we're still using that

02:10:19.800 --> 02:10:23.440
[Guest]: with the Cochin harbour, the schools, the buildings, the colleges, all of that is still

02:10:23.440 --> 02:10:24.440
[Guest]: there.

02:10:24.440 --> 02:10:27.360
[Guest]: And I was like, that deserves some sort of commemoration.

02:10:27.360 --> 02:10:31.560
[Guest]: So all the Travancore history you would find was pro Junior Rani's family, because they

02:10:31.560 --> 02:10:35.680
[Guest]: continue to live in Trivandrum, they continue to have a very important sort of profile there.

02:10:35.680 --> 02:10:36.840
[Guest]: They are influential people there.

02:10:36.840 --> 02:10:39.240
[Guest]: So all the local historians are focused on them.

02:10:39.240 --> 02:10:43.840
[Guest]: My job was to revise that record slightly and put things in the perspective, because

02:10:43.840 --> 02:10:44.840
[Amit Varma]: the record is clear.

02:10:44.840 --> 02:10:46.560
[Amit Varma]: To go beyond the seen into the unseen.

02:10:46.560 --> 02:10:47.560
[Amit Varma]: Yeah, correct.

02:10:47.560 --> 02:10:53.920
[Amit Varma]: No, the line that really stuck me from your story is the sort of the self awareness and

02:10:53.920 --> 02:10:59.520
[Amit Varma]: the reflective nature of the Senior Rani when she signs away her final property papers and

02:10:59.520 --> 02:11:01.240
[Amit Varma]: says, this is my freedom at midnight.

02:11:01.240 --> 02:11:05.520
[Amit Varma]: And it strikes me that, you know, the story you've told is from her childhood till you

02:11:05.520 --> 02:11:07.080
[Amit Varma]: know, she's out of the throne.

02:11:07.080 --> 02:11:11.280
[Amit Varma]: And it strikes me that there's a fantastic story there as well of giving up royalty and

02:11:11.280 --> 02:11:15.060
[Amit Varma]: learning to live as a normal person and coming to terms with all of that.

02:11:15.060 --> 02:11:20.080
[Amit Varma]: And I'm sure some of that of stripping the baggage of the past must also involve a lot

02:11:20.080 --> 02:11:23.360
[Amit Varma]: of self reflection, which would be, you know, really interesting in a book.

02:11:23.360 --> 02:11:26.520
[Amit Varma]: But that's really not a task for a historian, but a novelist or a poet.

02:11:26.520 --> 02:11:27.520
[Amit Varma]: It will do well in a novel.

02:11:27.520 --> 02:11:28.520
[Guest]: Exactly.

02:11:28.520 --> 02:11:31.480
[Guest]: See, the thing is, when you're doing a biography, your greatest challenge is trying to get into

02:11:31.480 --> 02:11:33.160
[Guest]: the mind of that person.

02:11:33.160 --> 02:11:36.000
[Guest]: And here I was a fairly young person starting at 19.

02:11:36.000 --> 02:11:39.320
[Guest]: And even when I finished, I was only in my mid 20s, trying to decipher the mind of a

02:11:39.320 --> 02:11:43.160
[Guest]: woman who had lived in a different world, who had died 30 years before me, I mean, five

02:11:43.160 --> 02:11:47.480
[Guest]: years before I was born, you know, and occupied such a different space altogether.

02:11:47.480 --> 02:11:48.480
[Guest]: And she's a woman.

02:11:48.480 --> 02:11:53.040
[Guest]: So it's like, it's not easy to sort of penetrate a mind that is, you know, so lost in time

02:11:53.040 --> 02:11:56.800
[Guest]: and so lost even in terms of its basic nature.

02:11:56.800 --> 02:12:00.320
[Guest]: But you know, I thought for me, it was a rewarding experience and the wealth of material.

02:12:00.320 --> 02:12:04.840
[Guest]: The one thing I think the vindication really is that, although she was treated badly and

02:12:04.840 --> 02:12:06.920
[Guest]: which is written out of history, the records were there.

02:12:06.920 --> 02:12:09.880
[Guest]: So for me, it was just a question of resurrecting her from the records.

02:12:09.880 --> 02:12:14.120
[Guest]: The records make it very clear that she suffered, that she was treated badly, that she went

02:12:14.120 --> 02:12:17.920
[Guest]: through everything from black magic to her money being reduced to a palace being taken

02:12:17.920 --> 02:12:18.920
[Guest]: over by others.

02:12:18.920 --> 02:12:21.600
[Guest]: And it tells you so much about human behavior as well.

02:12:21.600 --> 02:12:24.960
[Guest]: It tells you that even you can have all the power in the world, you can have all the money

02:12:24.960 --> 02:12:25.960
[Guest]: in the world.

02:12:25.960 --> 02:12:30.280
[Guest]: But decency is a quality that does not necessarily come to every human being.

02:12:30.280 --> 02:12:31.600
[Guest]: So how have her grandchildren read your book?

02:12:31.600 --> 02:12:32.600
[Guest]: How have they reacted?

02:12:32.600 --> 02:12:35.960
[Guest]: For them, a lot of them, it surprised a lot of them, they didn't know this.

02:12:35.960 --> 02:12:36.960
[Guest]: They didn't know a lot.

02:12:36.960 --> 02:12:39.320
[Guest]: I mean, they knew vaguely that she had suffered because she had come away to Bangalore.

02:12:39.320 --> 02:12:41.240
[Guest]: So they knew that their family's exodus to Bangalore.

02:12:41.240 --> 02:12:45.360
[Guest]: And even now in India, we have people who have coronations and they pretend to be Maharajas

02:12:45.360 --> 02:12:47.600
[Guest]: and they have these titles that they still use.

02:12:47.600 --> 02:12:51.880
[Guest]: And here is a woman in 1950s itself, the family gives up everything and moves up and doesn't

02:12:51.880 --> 02:12:52.880
[Guest]: go back.

02:12:52.880 --> 02:12:55.600
[Guest]: Like they, as one granddaughter told me, they don't have a spot of land where they can stick

02:12:55.600 --> 02:12:59.440
[Guest]: a needle and say, this is ours in a kingdom that their ancestors ruled for centuries,

02:12:59.440 --> 02:13:02.540
[Guest]: because that's the choice that their family made.

02:13:02.540 --> 02:13:06.320
[Guest]: Because they were not aware of all the details of the extent to which their grandmother had

02:13:06.320 --> 02:13:09.360
[Guest]: to face harassment and various problems, etc.

02:13:09.360 --> 02:13:13.680
[Guest]: They were not aware of the degree to which court intrigue could completely upset a person's

02:13:13.680 --> 02:13:14.680
[Amit Varma]: life.

02:13:14.680 --> 02:13:19.200
[Amit Varma]: Or even the things she achieved, like winning Gandhi's respect, governing so well, you know,

02:13:19.200 --> 02:13:23.680
[Amit Varma]: being so reformist in her thinking about caste and gender, however, she might have been in

02:13:23.680 --> 02:13:24.680
[Amit Varma]: personal life.

02:13:24.680 --> 02:13:29.880
[Guest]: All of that is pretty, I think they were surprised in many ways, in many ways by that.

02:13:29.880 --> 02:13:33.080
[Amit Varma]: One of the interesting things she also did was she struck down the matrilineal system

02:13:33.080 --> 02:13:34.080
[Guest]: by law.

02:13:34.080 --> 02:13:35.080
[Guest]: Irony, no?

02:13:35.080 --> 02:13:39.000
[Guest]: She inherited power through that system, but it was in her time that it was formally abolished,

02:13:39.000 --> 02:13:43.320
[Guest]: because by then the clamor for patriarchal families and nuclear families grew.

02:13:43.320 --> 02:13:46.700
[Guest]: The thing was matrilineal families were also joint families, so which means all the properties

02:13:46.700 --> 02:13:47.700
[Guest]: tied up.

02:13:47.700 --> 02:13:50.760
[Guest]: So as I said, the Irawas and the Christians are moneyed classes, they're moving ahead.

02:13:50.760 --> 02:13:53.100
[Guest]: So the Nayas felt we need to also move ahead.

02:13:53.100 --> 02:13:56.760
[Guest]: Now all you have is land, so you sell the land, which means land has to be partitioned.

02:13:56.760 --> 02:13:59.360
[Guest]: Partition means you have to break the joint family, which means the matrilineal family

02:13:59.360 --> 02:14:00.400
[Guest]: has to break.

02:14:00.400 --> 02:14:04.040
[Guest]: And also your education system, your new morality is telling you patriarchy is the way to go

02:14:04.040 --> 02:14:05.040
[Guest]: forward.

02:14:05.040 --> 02:14:07.580
[Guest]: So all things come together in 1825.

02:14:07.580 --> 02:14:11.840
[Guest]: This lady, Saitulakshmi Bai is the one who ironically ends up abolishing the matrilineal

02:14:11.840 --> 02:14:12.840
[Guest]: system.

02:14:12.840 --> 02:14:15.560
[Guest]: And in many ways, she's the last representative of that system.

02:14:15.560 --> 02:14:21.200
[Guest]: She her story is a story of how that that that conflict with an emerging new patriarchal

02:14:21.200 --> 02:14:25.040
[Guest]: morality upsets and reduces the position of matrilineal women.

02:14:25.040 --> 02:14:29.280
[Guest]: And the male Maharaja, who's her technically a nephew, and therefore lower to her in the

02:14:29.280 --> 02:14:33.760
[Guest]: palace, high in the family hierarchy, suddenly becomes the main person because he's a man.

02:14:33.760 --> 02:14:34.760
[Amit Varma]: And it's interesting.

02:14:34.760 --> 02:14:38.080
[Amit Varma]: She is the last person to climb on that branch, and then she cuts it off herself.

02:14:38.080 --> 02:14:42.080
[Amit Varma]: So that's really been very fascinating, and it's almost time to wrap it up.

02:14:42.080 --> 02:14:46.520
[Amit Varma]: But before we go, you know, looking at modern Kerala today, it's kind of interesting that

02:14:46.520 --> 02:14:51.680
[Amit Varma]: like you pointed out earlier, attitudes and social norms and mores that we think have

02:14:51.680 --> 02:14:56.160
[Amit Varma]: come down from time immemorial can often be very recent, like, for example, the Victorian

02:14:56.160 --> 02:14:57.920
[Amit Varma]: morality and all of that.

02:14:57.920 --> 02:15:01.680
[Amit Varma]: How much of that ancient Kerala, which you describe in your book through the middle years

02:15:01.680 --> 02:15:08.360
[Amit Varma]: of the century, the empower empowered women and so on, is actually present in modern Kerala?

02:15:08.360 --> 02:15:12.560
[Guest]: You see, you know, the hints are very clear, for example, Kerala has the India's highest

02:15:12.560 --> 02:15:13.560
[Guest]: divorce rate.

02:15:13.560 --> 02:15:16.680
[Guest]: That's partly because I think as a legacy of the majorly in the system, which is, by

02:15:16.680 --> 02:15:19.960
[Amit Varma]: the way, a great thing, because it means more women are empowered.

02:15:19.960 --> 02:15:20.960
[Guest]: They have agency.

02:15:20.960 --> 02:15:24.160
[Guest]: If you're in a bad marriage, leaving it is not taboo.

02:15:24.160 --> 02:15:27.440
[Amit Varma]: I once wrote a column saying we should celebrate rising divorce rates, which of course got

02:15:27.440 --> 02:15:31.320
[Guest]: me told because it's like, what the fuck, yeah, but as an indicator, it's always a great

02:15:31.320 --> 02:15:35.200
[Guest]: thing because it shows that women will not take nonsense from their husbands simply to

02:15:35.200 --> 02:15:36.200
[Guest]: stay in a marriage.

02:15:36.200 --> 02:15:39.760
[Guest]: A high divorce rate is a mark that at least the women have that much agency.

02:15:39.760 --> 02:15:44.480
[Guest]: They similarly, you know, people often say rape is highest in Kerala, reported rape,

02:15:44.480 --> 02:15:47.240
[Guest]: that is to say, women in Kerala feel that they can report it.

02:15:47.240 --> 02:15:50.160
[Guest]: And there will be consequences to the culprits for that.

02:15:50.160 --> 02:15:54.000
[Guest]: Whereas in some states of India, there's so much taboo that most women won't even report

02:15:54.000 --> 02:15:55.000
[Amit Varma]: it.

02:15:55.000 --> 02:15:59.200
[Guest]: So basically, there's just no point, you know, high, you know, rape thing on record is a

02:15:59.200 --> 02:16:04.080
[Guest]: sign again, that women are not, they don't feel like their life ends because of a violation

02:16:04.080 --> 02:16:06.080
[Guest]: of their of their person and their body.

02:16:06.080 --> 02:16:09.880
[Guest]: So there's, you know, there are advantages and you see markers like that, which speak

02:16:09.880 --> 02:16:10.880
[Guest]: to you.

02:16:10.880 --> 02:16:15.560
[Guest]: But they had lots of other weird thing, which is that the matrilineal system as it was fading.

02:16:15.560 --> 02:16:18.720
[Guest]: So my great grandmother, she went to school, because by then it was normal for girls to

02:16:18.720 --> 02:16:20.120
[Guest]: go to school.

02:16:20.120 --> 02:16:23.200
[Guest]: And what was interesting though, is this while girls were allowed to go to school, Kerala

02:16:23.200 --> 02:16:26.520
[Guest]: was one of the first places to allow girls to go to school because matrilineal permitted

02:16:26.520 --> 02:16:28.680
[Guest]: women literacy and education.

02:16:28.680 --> 02:16:31.640
[Guest]: That new system of education was a patriarchal one.

02:16:31.640 --> 02:16:35.080
[Guest]: So it was also the same textbooks and the same thing that subconsciously told these

02:16:35.080 --> 02:16:38.480
[Guest]: women, your job is to be good wives, your job is to be good mothers, and you must be

02:16:38.480 --> 02:16:41.060
[Guest]: maternal, let your husbands handle things like that.

02:16:41.060 --> 02:16:46.000
[Guest]: So it also ingrained a strange kind of patriarchy in Kerala, and that is also equally alive.

02:16:46.000 --> 02:16:49.560
[Guest]: So on the one hand, you do have women with agency, but you also have a deeply entrenched

02:16:49.560 --> 02:16:55.560
[Guest]: patriarchal mindset in Kerala now, entirely artificial, entirely born out of male insecurities.

02:16:55.560 --> 02:16:58.760
[Guest]: Because in the 19th century, these men felt like they had to control their women to be

02:16:58.760 --> 02:16:59.760
[Guest]: masculine.

02:16:59.760 --> 02:17:00.760
[Guest]: But that also exists simultaneously.

02:17:00.760 --> 02:17:04.840
[Guest]: So you have both things that actually exist in Kerala.

02:17:04.840 --> 02:17:08.800
[Guest]: But one of the things that advantages that the state has because it had rulers like Sethu

02:17:08.800 --> 02:17:13.640
[Guest]: Lakshmibai is that Kerala is talking language, the language of the right to internet, because

02:17:13.640 --> 02:17:16.340
[Guest]: there's no roti, kappadam, makan problem in Kerala.

02:17:16.340 --> 02:17:18.480
[Guest]: These things were already handled a while ago.

02:17:18.480 --> 02:17:21.760
[Guest]: Kerala is the one state where land reforms did work, it actually meant something.

02:17:21.760 --> 02:17:24.800
[Guest]: Earlier, in many North Indian states, land reforms were just on paper.

02:17:24.800 --> 02:17:27.400
[Guest]: In reality, families managed to find loopholes and jump through it.

02:17:27.400 --> 02:17:31.840
[Guest]: Whereas in Kerala, land reforms actually did take place and most of the land was in many

02:17:31.840 --> 02:17:34.920
[Guest]: ways redistributed and other people ended up getting lots of land.

02:17:34.920 --> 02:17:39.000
[Guest]: So there are changes in Kerala that were born out of not only the communists who did a great

02:17:39.000 --> 02:17:43.320
[Guest]: job at least for as far as welfarism is concerned, but also the previous royal rulers.

02:17:43.320 --> 02:17:47.400
[Guest]: Because under pressure from the colonial state, under pressure from a lot of missionaries,

02:17:47.400 --> 02:17:52.000
[Guest]: they had no option but to invest in education, but to slowly peel back social inequalities,

02:17:52.000 --> 02:17:56.080
[Guest]: build up infrastructure in the state and that has therefore kept the state in a very, let's

02:17:56.080 --> 02:17:59.320
[Guest]: say, enviable position as far as human life is concerned.

02:17:59.320 --> 02:18:01.560
[Guest]: It has issues in manufacturing and industry.

02:18:01.560 --> 02:18:05.480
[Guest]: But overall, you know, life in Kerala, you enter Kerala, the first thing you'll see is

02:18:05.480 --> 02:18:09.560
[Guest]: ads for fabric, textiles and gold, because it's one of the biggest consumer states in

02:18:09.560 --> 02:18:12.880
[Guest]: the country for gold and textiles, because people have disposable income.

02:18:12.880 --> 02:18:16.040
[Guest]: You drive through Kerala villages, everybody has a pakka house, most of these houses are

02:18:16.040 --> 02:18:19.600
[Guest]: flamboyant houses, often, you know, financed by Dubai money.

02:18:19.600 --> 02:18:24.000
[Guest]: But the point is that people have a lifestyle that is fairly superior.

02:18:24.000 --> 02:18:30.380
[Amit Varma]: In fact, I read on the internet recently that there was a survey of the fastest growing

02:18:30.380 --> 02:18:33.600
[Guest]: cities in the world and three of the top 10 were Kerala.

02:18:33.600 --> 02:18:38.520
[Amit Varma]: And you could argue four if Sharjah is to be included.

02:18:38.520 --> 02:18:41.800
[Amit Varma]: So let's move from the state of Kerala to the state of Manipally.

02:18:41.800 --> 02:18:46.480
[Amit Varma]: You told me the last time we met, that you wanted to write three books before 30.

02:18:46.480 --> 02:18:47.480
[Amit Varma]: That is done.

02:18:47.480 --> 02:18:49.000
[Amit Varma]: You have written three books before 30.

02:18:49.000 --> 02:18:54.480
[Amit Varma]: Is the rest of your life a long, slow decline like Sethu Lakshmibai, or what are you working

02:18:54.480 --> 02:18:55.480
[Guest]: on now?

02:18:55.480 --> 02:18:56.480
[Guest]: No, I am working on something.

02:18:56.480 --> 02:18:59.360
[Guest]: In fact, the research is more or less done, I just have to digest the research and start

02:18:59.360 --> 02:19:00.360
[Guest]: writing.

02:19:00.360 --> 02:19:02.900
[Guest]: So my deadline is 2022 to publish the book.

02:19:02.900 --> 02:19:05.880
[Guest]: So but that is a lot of work, because I'm also doing my PhD.

02:19:05.880 --> 02:19:10.040
[Guest]: So I'm on leave at the moment, but I resume at the end of the summer.

02:19:10.040 --> 02:19:12.120
[Guest]: So I have to focus on PhD and my writing.

02:19:12.120 --> 02:19:14.400
[Guest]: And this is perhaps my most ambitious book.

02:19:14.400 --> 02:19:17.160
[Guest]: In many ways, it will probably be also my most controversial book.

02:19:17.160 --> 02:19:20.820
[Guest]: I mean, so far, you know, writing about forgotten Sultans of the Deccan, forgotten Queen of

02:19:20.820 --> 02:19:21.820
[Unknown]: Triumph.

02:19:21.820 --> 02:19:26.040
[Guest]: You can say some important things, but you know, it doesn't upset the political weirdos

02:19:26.040 --> 02:19:27.040
[Guest]: that are out there.

02:19:27.040 --> 02:19:31.480
[Guest]: But the next one, I have a feeling might just get a few rotten eggs to sort of perk up and

02:19:31.480 --> 02:19:33.600
[Guest]: think my God, how dare he say this.

02:19:33.600 --> 02:19:37.080
[Guest]: So there is there is that project underway, but it will take me a while to actually, you

02:19:37.080 --> 02:19:38.080
[Guest]: know, complete it.

02:19:38.080 --> 02:19:40.480
[Amit Varma]: Well, it's a pleasure having you on the scene and the unseen.

02:19:40.480 --> 02:19:43.680
[Amit Varma]: I hope when your next controversial book gets done, do come here.

02:19:43.680 --> 02:19:46.240
[Guest]: This is one platform which will still welcome your heretical views.

02:19:46.240 --> 02:19:49.640
[Guest]: I'll let you know as soon as it's out so we can do a scene and the unseen session.

02:19:49.640 --> 02:19:51.920
[Amit Varma]: Yeah, thanks a lot, Manu.

02:19:51.920 --> 02:19:53.160
[Amit Varma]: Thanks.

